Commentary: Roach starts with an outswinging full ball outside off, Burns watches the first ball of the day and leaves the ball alone.
Very full delivery outside off, swinging away from the batsman, Burns has no problems in leaving the ball alone.
Strays down the line this time! Good length ball down the leg side, Burns looks to flick but fails to get any bat on it.
Much better from Roach! Good length ball outside off, moving away, Burns leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Excellent start from Roach! This is a brilliant delivery! Good length ball outside off, Burns looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Roach finishes this over by bowling a good length ball on off, Burns pushes it to point. Good start from Roach. Maiden to start with.
Poor start from Gabriel! He probably lost his run-up! Full delivery way down the leg side, Sibley leaves it alone and Dowrich dives to his left to collect it.

FIVE WIDES! This is a terrible start from Gabriel! Not the start he would have liked! Good length ball down the leg side, Sibley leaves it alone. Dowrich dives to his left but fails to collect it. The ball rolls to the fine leg region for 5 wides.
Length ball down the leg side again, Sibley looks to flick but misses. Gabriel has to get his line correct.
This is a much better line from Gabriel! Good length ball outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to it.
Full delivery on off, Sibley prods forward and defends it to the point region.
This time Gabriel bowls a back of a length delivery outside off, Sibley makes a leave to this one.
First runs off the bat! Good length ball on middle, Sibley flicks it to square leg and gets off the mark with a single. 6 runs from Gabriel's first.
Full delivery outside off, Sibley makes another leave to this one.
Length ball on middle, Sibley stands tall and defends it out off the back foot.
Full delivery outside off, Sibley drives it to cover for a single.
Fullish ball on middle, Burns pushes it back to the bowler.
Length ball outside off, Burns shoulders arms to it.
Roach dishes a full delivery outside off, swinging away, Burns watches the ball go by as he leaves it alone.
Another one down the leg side! Gabriel bowls this one straying down the leg side, Sibley leaves it alone.
Full delivery on middle, Dom flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Gabriel dishes a full ball outside off, Rory lets the ball through to the keeper.
Good length ball on middle, Burns flicks it to mid-wicket. Rory has faced 11 deliveries but is yet to get off the mark.
Good length ball outside off, Burns shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length ball on middle, Burns flicks it to short leg.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Good length ball on off, angling in sharply. Sibley looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Roach puts in a huge appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested. West Indies do not take the review and it is a good decision as the Ball Tracker shows that it missing the stumps.
Length ball outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
Full delivery outside off, Sibley lets the ball go to the keeper.
Roach dishes a full delivery on middle, Dom pushes it towards mid on.
Outside off, Sibley makes a leave to this one.
WIDE! Wayward from Roach! Good length ball outside off, Sibley does not bother to play at that one. Wide signaled.
On a length on middle, Sibley works it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Burns shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length ball outside off, Rory has no problems in leaving it alone.
Full delivery outside off, Burns lets it go to the keeper.
Good length delivery outside off, Burns makes another leave to this one.
Good length ball on the pads, Burns looks to flick but misses.
The batsman tries flicking a ball that is down the leg side.
Joseph starts with a fuller delivery on off, Sibley defends it off the front foot.
Joseph pulls his length back and delivers this outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to it.
Another one outside off, Sibley is not keen in playing that.
Good running! Back of a length delivery around off, Sibley taps it towards cover and takes off for a quick single. Burns responds as well allowing them to get it with ease.
Alzarri bowls it on middle and off, Burns defends it towards point.
Slightly fuller on middle and off, Burns turns it to the on side and gets a single.
Good length delivery on off, Burns defends it with a straight bat.
On the pads, Burns tucks it to the leg side.
Another one on the pads, Burns glances it towards fine leg and gets a couple.
Outside off, Burns leaves it alone.
Holder bowls it outside off asking  Rory to drive but he is calm enough to leave it.
Away from the off pole, RB leaves it.
Fuller outside off, Sibley leaves it .
Ohh! Full and angling in a bit, Sibley is late to defend but quick enough to get his bat down in time. The ball hits the lower half of his bat and goes towards second slip.
On the pads, Sibley flicks it to the on side for a single.
Fuller on off, Burns defends it with a straight bat.
Once again Alzarri bowls full and on the off pole, Burns gently pushes it wide of mid off and gets a couple as Campbell cleans it up.
Good length ball on off, Burns blocks it off his back foot to get through the over.
Outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
On off, Sibley defends it off the back foot.
Another one away from the stumps, Sibley is in no rush to play at that.
Good length ball on off, Sibley defends it off the back foot.
Length ball around off, Sibley looks to defend but the ball shapes away and goes off the edge towards point and they take a run.
Good ball! Length delivery outside off, it pitches and straightens. Burns looks to defend but misses. Lucky not to edge it.
Full on middle and off, Sibley defends it towards mid on.
On off, Sibley blocks it.
Good length delivery on off, it jags back in. Sibley looks to defend but misses and gets hit high on his thigh pad.
Length ball around off, this one shapes away. DS shoulders arms to it.
Another one on a length around off, Sibley defends it.
On off, Dom defends it to see off the over. Maiden over from Alzarri.
First boundary off the bat for England! Holder misses his line and sprays one down the leg side, Burns flicks it fine down the leg side. Away from the man at fine leg and gets a boundary.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Burns hangs back and cuts it through point and gets three as the fielder mops is up before the ropes.
Good length ball on off, Sibley defends it off the back foot.
Once again Holder hits the deck hard on off, Sibley defends it.
On middle, Sibley flicks it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, Dom leaves it alone.
Good shot! Full outside off, Burns leans on his drive and hits it through covers. The ball does not have the legs to reach the fence as the fielder cleans it up. The batters take three.
Good length ball on off, Sibley defends it towards mid on.
Outside off, Dom leaves it alone.
On off, Sibley blocks it with a dead bat.
Outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
Length ball outside off, Sibley punches it towards cover-point and keeps the strike with a single.
Chase starts with a floated delivery on middle, Sibley flicks it towards mid-wicket and gets a single.

OUT! Three reds and Burns has to go! Chase has done exactly what he was brought on to do. Right on the stroke of Lunch. England lose Burns and a review as well. Flighted delivery pitching on middle, Burns looks to defend but the ball does not spin and straightens on after pitching. Burns misses it and gets hit on the front pad. The West Indies players put in a huge appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Burns has a brief chat with Sibley and then decides to take it upstairs. Replay rolls in and first it is confirmed no bat is involved. Time for Ball Tracker and it shows all reds. Burns has to walk back and he takes away a review as well. The players all follow him as it is Lunch on Day 1!

OUT! TAKEN! A wicket before the Lunch break and a wicket after it! Nothing better could the Windies have asked for. Roston Chase gets his second and it is  Zak who played really well in the last game bags a golden duck. A soft dismissal to be honest. It lands on middle, Crawley looks to work it on the leg side but does so uppishly towards leg slip who takes a sharp catch. England find themself in a spot of bother here. Chase is on a hat-trick.
Big turn! But down the leg side. It lands on middle and spins into the batter. Root leaves it.
On the pads, Root pads it away.
A dot to end a double wicket over! on middle, Root works it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.
Another delivery outside off, left alone.

EDGED BUT DOES NOT CARRY! Fuller and outside off, Sibley looks to drive but it goes off the outside edge, it lands just short of the fielder at second slip who fails to stop it. He does get a had to it so it does not get to the third man fence. Two taken.

NOT OUT! The impact indeed is outside off! A review probably in desperation. It lands outside off and comes back in a little. Root decides late to defend it, probably looking at the movement. He is struck on the pad. An appeal but the umpire turns it down. Holder signals the 'T'. Replays show that the on-field call is the right one.
Outside off, left alone.
One more delivery outside off, Root keeps it out. Another good over for Roach.
On off, blocked.
An appeal but a muted one! This lands on off and turns back in. Sibley looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal but it is turned down. Too high and doing a little too much.
On off, kept out.
Floats it up on middle, Sibley is solid in defense.

Confusion but safe! It is worked with the turn towards square leg. Root sets off, Sibley is a touch late to take off. The fielder there is off balance and hence the throw at the non-striker's end is not a good one.
Quicker and on middle, Root goes back and keeps it out.
BEATEN! Beauty from Roach! Goes wide of the crease and angles it into the off pole. Gets it to straighter after pitching. Beats the outside edge of Sibley's bat.
A little too full and a little too straight, Sibley works it through square leg for two.
Outside off, left alone.
Once again a little too straight, this is worked through square leg for two again.
Gets it right this time, bowls it just outside off, not played at.
On off, defended nicely.
Floated on off, Root blocks it.
Shorter and on the pads, Root bends his back knee and pulls it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Spin and a good amount of it on this one. It is pitched on leg and spins in, Sibley looks to flick but misses. Dowrich gets excited but fails to gather the ball.
Floated on off, Sibley tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Short and wide outside off, Sibley late cuts it towards third man and gets a couple.
Flighted off spinner on middle and leg, Sibley turns it to the leg side. Luckily it falls short of leg slip.
On a length and around off, kept out.
EDGY FOUR! Lucky for Root! He flashes at this one way outside off, it flies off the outside edge past the diving fielder at gully and into the third man fence.
BEATEN! Loose from Root again. Gets away with it though. Shorter and outside off, Root goes after it away from the body but fails to put bat on ball.
Does the right thing this time by letting the ball outside off go to the keeper.
On off, defended.
Worked with the angle towards mid-wicket for one.
BEATEN! Fails to read the length there! This is quite full. Root goes back to it and tries to defend but the ball goes straight on and beats the outside edge.
Shorter and around off, Root goes back and guides it to point.
Shorter again, easy for Root. He loves playing on the back foot, does so again and cuts it through point for three.
On the pads, it is worked to short leg.
Down the leg side, left alone.
A single now as Sibley keeps strike by getting to the other end. He worked this one towards mid-wicket.
On off, solidly blocked.
Outside off, left alone.
Shorter and around off, it is pushed through covers for one.
Back of a length and on off, kept out.
Outside off, not played at.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot. The batsmen have run through for a single.
Nicely played! Out comes the sweep shot, it is through square leg for two. 50 comes up for England.
On off, blocked.
Shorter and around middle, it is pulled through mid-wicket for one.
Worked with the turn by Sibley this time for one.
On the pads again, it is worked on the leg side.
A dot to end as Root goes right back and works it to mid-wicket.
Good line and length this from Roach! Fuller delivery outside off, it shapes away just a tad. Sibley looks to defend but misses.
This time it is full and on middle and off, Sibley is quite happy to get it there as he flicks this through mid-wicket for a couple.
Good length ball on off, Dom defends it to on the leg side.
Length ball outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
On the fourth stump line, Sibley knows his off pole and leaves it.
Solid defense to end the over. Length ball on off, Sibley blocks it towards mid off and sees off the over.
Starts off well! On a length and around off, blocked.
Another delivery outside off, left alone.
Close! Fuller and outside off, Root goes after it away from his body. It goes off the inside edge, past the off pole and down to fine leg for one.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
Outside off, comes in a bit but not enough to make the batter play. The keeper has difficulty in collecting it cleanly and two runs are taken.
Once again Dowrich fails to take it cleanly as it is moving after passing the batter. It is outside off, Sibely lets it be.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
Another one which attacks the off pole, kept out.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one outside off, root pushes it to point.
FOUR! Bread and butter stuff for Root! It is on his pads, he just puts bat to ball and it races to the mid-wicket fence.
Good comeback! Roach lands it outside off and gets it to nip back in. Root is hit near the crouch as he fails to put bat on ball.
On off, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, Sibley strides forward and keeps it out.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.
Down the leg side, Root lets it be.
Another stifled appeal! Short and down the leg side, Root looks to pull but misses.
Outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
Away swinger outside off, Sibley is not interested in that.

Full on off and swinging away. Sibley looks to push it towards mid off but gets a thick outside edge which goes along the ground to the right of gully. The fielder fails to stop it and the batter takes a run.
Length ball outside off, Root shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length delivery, Joe defends it.
On off, Root blocks it.
Fullish and on off, it is driven to mid off.
Pulls his length back slightly, defended nicely.
Outside off, not played at.
One more ball outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Up and over! Shorter in length and width on offer. Sibley throws his bat at it. It flies off the outside edge over the gully fielder and into the third man fence.
A very full ball on off, jammed out.
Outside off, Root is not interested in playing the delivery.
Solid! On off, Root prods forward and keeps it out.
One more delivery outside off, left alone.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On middle, Root works it off a thick inside edge through square leg for two.
Outside off, left alone.
This lands on middle and then comes back in sharply. Hits Sibley on his thigh pad as he looks to flick.
Outside off, Sibley guides it through point for two.
That ball has struck the batsman on the thigh-pad.
Down the leg side, Sibley fails to put bat on ball.
On off, kept out.
A double to end as this is driven through mid off.

On the pads, Root flicks it through mid-wicket. The fielder gives it a chase and pulls it before the ropes. There is a slight hesitation from Sibley and Root for the third but the throw is a wide one so no danger and they get the third with ease.
Outside off, Sibley leaves it.

EDGED AND FOUR! Full outside off and shaping away, Sibley looks to push it straight towards mid off away from his body but the ball takes the outside edge and goes wide of the man at gully and into the fence. 50-run stand also comes up between these two batters.
Now offers a calm leave to the delivery outside off.
Away from the stumps and Dom shoulders arms to it.
Fuller on off, Dom blocks it.
Outside off, Root drives square on the off side towards point.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! There is the wicket Windies so desperately needed. Root is out of here. He never actually looked settled, he always looked rusty and now finally falls. The partnership which was building nicely has been broken. It is the sucker ball which does the trick. Full and outside off, Root goes to drive but does not get his front foot towards the pitch of the delivery, he ends up edging it to Holder at second slip. Joseph gets the big fish and the Windies are elated.
Full and on middle, Stokes is off the mark as he works it through mid-wicket for two.
Left on a length! Just a back of a length delivery outside off, it is left alone.
Wider outside off, left alone.
Another couple to end an action-packed over. Fuller and on middle, it is worked through mid-wicket for two.
Length delivery around off, Sibley pushes it to mid on.
Good length delivery on off, Sibley blocks it with a straight bat.
Full outside off, Sibley looks to defend but does so off the outer half of his bat.
On the fourth stump line, Sibley lets it carry to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone by DS.
Another one left alone with ease by Dom.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Another one away from Stokes he lets it carry to Dowrich behind the stumps.
Full and straight on off, Stokes defends it with a straight bat.
Beauty! Good length ball pitching outside off, it nips back in sharply. Stokes looks to play it with a straight bat but the ball jags in and goes right between the bat and pad to the keeper.
Back of a length on off, Stokes defends it towards point.
Full toss but Joseph gets away with it. It is on off, Stokes drives it but finds mid off.
Down the leg side, Sibley looks to flick but misses. This is the area Dom has gone out to previously.
Yorker on off, Sibley manages to jam it out.
Full on off, Dom defends it with a straight bat.
Good length ball outside off, Dom blocks it
Length ball swinging away, Sibley defends it towards point.
Edged but safe! Good length ball around off and swinging away. Sibley looks to defend it with soft hands but gets a thick outside edge which goes away from gully and they take a couple.
Full outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Length ball on off, Stokes defends it.
On the pads, Stokes flicks it to the on side and gets a couple.
Good length ball on off, Stokes looks to defend but it goes off the inner half of his bat behind square on the leg side for a single.
On off, defended by Sibley.
Length ball on off, Sibley blocks it back to Alzarri.
Full on off, Stokes defends it.
Outside off, BS leaves it.
Very full on off, Ben defends it.
Full on off, Stokes blocks it. Ohhs and ahhs from the West Indies players.
Outside off, left alone by the vice captain.
Comes around the wicket and bowls it away from the stumps, Stokes does not disturb that.
Good length ball away from the stumps, Sibley leaves it.
Full and on the stumps, Sibley blocks it.
Very full on off, Dom bends his back and dabs it down the ground.
Full on middle and leg, Sibley flicks it but finds mid-wicket.
Outside off, Dom shoulders arms to it.
On the hips, Sibley flicks it towards square leg and gets a single.

Pleasant drive. Full and wide outside off, Sibley leans on his front foot and drives it through covers. The ball does not have the legs to reach the fence and the fielder cleans it up allowing the batters to take three.
On the hips, Stokes tucks it to the leg side for a single.
Good length ball on off and middle, it nips in. Sibley looks to defend but it goes towards mid-wicket off the inner half of his bat for a single.
Comes around the wicket and bowls full on off to the left-hander. Stokes defends it.
Good length ball on off, Ben blocks.
Oh! Good length delivery around off, Stokes expects it to come back in but it shapes away off the surface. He looks to defend but gets beaten.
A little too wide outside off to make the batter play.
Fuller and on middle, it is pushed to mid on.
Back of a length and on off, Sibley stands tall and keeps it out.
A little too wide again outside off, looking to suck Sibley into a loose shot but the batter lets it be.
Bowls this one from close to the wicket, it is on middle, Sibley strokes it to mid on.
Outside off, left alone.
Slips one down the leg side, the keeper fails to collect it cleanly with a dive and two runs taken. Byes signaled.
On off, defended nicely.
Works it with the angle towards mid-wicket.
Firm drive but for no runs!! Stokes takes a few steps down the track and coverts it into a full ball. He drives it crisply to mid off.
Outside off, not played at.
Outside off, left alone.
Length and outside off, Sibley makes a leave.
A little too straight, this is worked through square leg for two. 100-up for England.
On off, defended nicely.
One more delivery outside off, Sibley lets it be.
Extremely full! This one shapes away. Sibley looks to jam it out but it goes off the outer half towards gully.
Well left in the end! This starts around off and then shapes away late. Sibley watches it carefully and lets it be.
Outside off, left alone.
Bowls another one outside off, not played at.
Third delivery in a row which is outside off, need not plat at it.
Another leave as this is once again outside off.
5 leaves in a row as it is bowled outside off again.
An over full of leaves as Roach has bowled all the deliveries outside off.
Flatter and on off, defended.
Was that a chance? Not sure. This is on middle, Sibley works it towards short leg firmly. It hits him, not sure if on the bounce or directly but then lobs away from the fielder.

Was that a catch now? Chase does feel so. It is the straighter one outside off. Sibley defends for the turn. It goes on the with the arm, hits something on its way. Dowrich fails to collect it as he starts appealing. He felt it was off the pad. Not sure as of now.
On off, defended nicely.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Little short and on middle, Sibley works it through mid-wicket for two.
Fires it outside off, left alone.
On off, kept out.
Way too wide outside off, left alone again.
Fires it full on off, Stokes pushes it to mid off.
Width on offer again, this is slapped through covers for one.
A dot to end as this is worked towards mid-wicket.
Fires it on the pads, it is worked towards mid-wicket.
SIX! Enough of blocking, says Stokes. He steps down the track, doesn't quite get to the pitch of the ball but still goes ahead with the shot. Hits it over the bowler's head for a biggie.

In the air... safe! This lands on off and then grips in the surface. Stokes is a touch early in the shot. He looks to force it on the off side but it goes off the inner half, uppishly but well short of mid on.
Leading edge! A soft one. On middle, Stokes looks to flick it against the turn. It goes off the leading edge but short of any fielder on the off side.
Fires this one on the pads, Stokes uses the pace and works it fine on the leg side. Three taken.
Floated ball on middle, Sibley keeps it out and that will be TEA ON DAY 1!
Good length delivery on off, Stokes blocks it off his back foot.
Length ball on off, Ben blocks it.
On off, Stokes pushes it to mid off.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Full on off, Stokes pushes it to mid off.
Outside off, Ben leaves it alone to get through the over.
Floated on off, Sibley blocks it.
On the pads, Dom flicks it to the leg side.
Down the leg side, Sibley leaves it.
Flighted on off, Dom looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Ben defends it.
The ball is down the leg side but the batsman still goes after it.
NO BALL! Roach oversteps as he delivers this ball. It is outside off and Ben has no business with it.
Away from the stumps and Stokes is happy to leave it.
On the fourth stump line, Ben has nothing to do with it.
Length delivery on off, Stokes punches it to cover.
Flighted on off, Sibley defends it.
Floated on off, Sibley defends it.
On the pads, Dom flicks it to the on side.
Flighted on off, DS blocks it.
On the pads, Sibley turns it to the on side and gets to the other end.
Floated around off, Stokes looks t defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Good length ball outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off, kept out.
Another one outside off, not played at.
Shorter and around off, this is pushed towards cover.
On the pads, Sibley works it through square leg for two.
On off, blocked.
Fired on the pads, Stokes looks to sweep but mises to get hit on the pads.
On middle, kept out.
This is hit through mid on for three.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Worked off the pads through the leg side for one.
FOUR! Good shot from Sibley! Length delivery on middle and leg, Sibley says thank yu very much and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Good length delivery this time outside off, Sibley looks to cut but does not time it well.
Length delivery around off, it shapes away. Sibley looks to defend but gets beaten.
Outside off, Sibley leaves it with confidence.
Away from the off stump and Sibley leaves it alone.
Ohh! Good length ball outside off, Sibley looks to have a feel of it but gets beaten.
Flighted on off, Stokes pushes it to mid on.
On the pads, Stokes turns it towards backward square leg and gets to the other end.

Bit of confusion and a better throw would have made it interesting. On the pads, Sibley flicks it and the ball deflects towards mid-wicket off the short leg fielder. Sibley comes halfway for a run but Stokes sends him back. The throw from the fielder is a poor one and Sibley is in with his dive as Dowrich cannot gather the throw.
Slightly shorter on off, Sibley pushes it to mid off.
Floated around off, Sibley defends it.
Tossed up on off, Dom blocks it.
Good length delivery outside off, Stokes looks to defend but the away shape makes him miss it.
Outside off and this time Stokes leaves it.
Well bowled! Good length delivery outside off, the ball pitches and straightens. Stokes looks to defend but misses it. Lucky as a similar delivery got better of Stokes at Southampton.
Length ball around off, this one comes back in. Stokes looks to defend but misses and gets hit high on the thigh pad.
Outside off, left alone by the English all-rounder.
Full on off and middle, Stokes flicks it towards mid-wicket and gets a couple.
Flighted on off, Sibley defends it.
Tossed up on off, Sibley flicks it towards mid-wicket and gets a single. Easy one this time as there is no mix-up.
Flatter and on off, this one sits up on the pitch. Stokes looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto his pad. The ball lobs but falls in front of first slip.
On the pads, this time Ben manages to flick it nicely and gets a single.
Tossed up on off, Sibley blocks it.
On the leg side, Sibley flicks it to the leg side and gets a single.
Outside off, it stays low. Sibley looks to push at it but it sneaks under the bat.
Outside off, left alone.
BEATEN! Lovely from Holder! He starts this one outside off and then gets it to shape away, The batter looks to defend but misses.
Outside off, not played at.
Another one outside off, left alone.
Slides it onto the pads, Sibley looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal but the umpire shakes his head. An ambitious appeal that.
Sweeps it brilliantly through square leg for a couple.
Fuller and on middle, it is pushed towards mid on for two.
Outside off, left alone.
Fires it on off, it is kept out.
FOUR! Swept hard! On middle, Stokes brings out the sweep and nails it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Outside off, not played at.
On the pads, Stokes looks to flick but misses. It hits the pads and rolls towards fine leg. A couple of leg byes taken.
Good length and on off, defended.
A big booming inswinger from outside off, Stokes is solid in defense.
Ohhh! This one tails back in from outside off, Stokes looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On middle, it is worked through mid-wicket for no runs.
Looks to drag this delivery outside leg by playing the reverse sweep but misses.
On middle,kept out.
Works this with the turn towards deep square leg for one.
Slower through the air but outside off, left alone.
Quicker and on middle, defended back to the bowler.
On the pads, Sibley flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, Sibley looks to defend but it jags back in much more than he anticipated and gets an inside edge onto his thigh pads.
Test match line and length this. Fuller outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
On off, Sibley blocks it.
Once again Sibley shows he is in no rush and defends it.
On the pads, Sibley looks to flick but the ball goes on the leg side off his thigh pad and they take a leg bye.
Floated on middle, Sibley tucks it to the leg side.
On middle, Sibley turns it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Sibley looks to reverse sweep but misses it. The ball kisses his pads and Dowrich misses it too allowing them to steal three leg byes.
Floated on off, Stokes defends it.
Floated on off, Stokes nudges it to cover.

FOUR! Brilliant from Stokes. That's how you hit a reverse sweep, Sibley. Darted full on middle and leg, Stokes gets in position and shows how quick his hands are as he hits it towards backward point for a boundary.
Wild start from Joseph. He bowls it full and very wide outside off. Dowrich does well diving to his right and stopping the ball.
Full again on off, Sibley looks to drive but gets an outside edge. It goes through point. The fielder in the deep does well to stop it. The batsmen get three.
Full on off, Stokes defends it.
Fuller on off, Stokes plays it to mid on.
On the pads, Stokes flicks it to the on side but finds the fielder.
On middle, Stokes defends it towards mid-wicket.
Flat and short outside off, Sibley cuts it through point and gets three.
Floated on off, Stokes pushes it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, Stokes milks it to long on and rotates the strike.
Flighted on off, Sibley looks to defend but does so off the inner half of his bat.
On off, Sibley whips it but finds mid-wicket.
Short outside off, Sibley punches it wide of cover-point and gets a couple.
Attacking shot from Stokes. Shorter outside off, Stokes pulls but finds mid-wicket.
On off, Stokes defends it.
On the pads, Stokes flicks it to the on side but once again finds a man.
Joseph bangs it in short, Stokes pulls it but there is protection in the deep so just a run.
Length ball outside off, Sibley plays it to the left of mid-wicket and calls for a quick single. Campbell there dives and ensures that there is only a single.
Full on off, Stokes pushes it to mid on.
Starts nicely! Good length delivery outside off, Sibley expects it to come back in but it straightens and misses the edge of Dom's bat.
NO BALL! Shannon oversteps his line. He bowls it full on middle, Sibbley flicks it through mid-wicket and gets a couple.
Very full on off, Sibley defends it.

EDGED AND DROPPED! Gabriel comes and almost made an impact! Holder who is usually a great fielder has dropped a regulation catch at slip. Full and outside off, it comes in a bit. First real error from Sibley as he looks to defend this. It takes the outside edge and goes quickly to second slip. Holder there may have got outdone by the pace at which the ball came and the ball goes in and out of his hand. How costly will this prove to be?
Outside off, Dom leaves it alone.
Length ball on off, DS plays it to point.
Good length ball on off, Sibley taps it towards mid on and calls for quick single. The batters take a quick run as Alzarri Joseph there is a bit on his heels.
Length ball around off, Sibley tucks it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, Dom blocks it.
Away from the stumps, Sibley does not disturb the ball on its way to the keeper.
Down the leg side, Sibley looks to flick but misses.
Length ball around off, Sibley defends it.
Lapse in concentration. Full on off and middle, Sibley flicks it towards mid-wicket. Campbell there misjudges it and ends up misfielding it allowing the batters to take three as he cleans it up.
On the pads, Sibley flicks it to the leg side and gets a single.
On middle, Stokes defends it to mid on.
WIDE! This one has gone straight to Holder at second slip. It is outside off and keeps going away. Holder takes it at second slip and also gets hurt in the process.
Outside off and in the limits this time. Stokes leaves it alone.
Full on off, Stokes defends it.
Very full on off and middle, Stokes turns it towards fine leg and gets a single.
Yorker on off, Sibley jams it out and looks for a single but decides against it. Good call!
Good length and on  middle, defended. The umpire once again has a look at the danger area, walks back with no warning.
Good length and on off, defended.
Fuller and on off, it is driven to mid on.
Back of a length and on off, Stokes stays back and defends it onto the ground.
Hits the length again and lands it on off, Stokes keeps it out.
Slightly shorter this time and on off, Stokes pushes it towards wide mid off and takes an easy run.
Outside off, not played at.
WIDE! Short and way too wide outside off, Stokes pulls out of the shot and lets it go through to the keeper. Wided.
FOUR! Easy-peasy! Full and on middle, Stokes just clips it with utmost ease through mid-wicket and it races away. Waiting for the bad balls is Big Ben and putting them away in style.
Gets way with one there does Gabriel! Short and outside off, Stokes looks to pull but fails to beat wide short mid on.
NO BALL! Gabriel has overstepped! He bowls this one down the leg side.
WIDE! Gabriel isn't at 100 percent and that can be made out. He bowls another one way wide outside off. Wided.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed towards mid off.
Angled into the pads, it is worked towards fine leg for one.
On off, kept out.
Fuller and around off, Stokes looks to drive but it goes off the outer half through point for three. Fifty up for Big Ben. Came in when his team needed him to score and does so.
Another three! Fuller and outside off, Sibley strokes it through point and takes three.
FOUR! Too easy! Runs flowing! On the pads, it is worked down towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
On middle, it is worked towards mid-wicket.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
One more three! End of an expensive over! Shorter and around off, Stokes pushes it through covers for three runs.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Another one away from the pole, Ben does not disturb that.
Repeat of the previous two deliveries. Holder wants Stokes to drive but Ben is happy to resist that temptation.
Outside off, shouldered arms to it.
On the fourth stump line, Stokes lets it carry to the keeper.
An over of left alone as the last ball is no different.
Length ball outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, left alone by DS.
Full outside off, Sibley drives it but the fielder at cover dives to his right and saves runs for his side.
On the pads, Sibley flicks it towards backward square leg and gets a couple.
A lot of movement on this one. It is down the leg side and once the ball is past the stumps it shapes away, wrong footing Dowrich behind the stumps.
Fuller on off, Sibley drives it to point.
Good length ball on off, Stokes blocks it.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
On the fourth stump line, Ben shoulders arms to it.
Down the leg side, Stokes looks to flick but misses. Good take by Dowrich.
Back to bowling outside off, Stokes has no qualms leaving it.
Once again outside off, this one shapes away from Stokes past the stumps. Dowrich dives and makes a great save.
Good length delivery outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, Dom leaves it alone.
FOUR! Low full toss on middle, Sibley works it away to the leg side and the ball races away to the fence. Sibley moves into his 80s with that.
Fullish ball way outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
Outside off, left alone by Dom.
Away from Sibley meaning he won't bother that.
Outside off, the English opener lets it be.
On the pads, Stokes glances it off his hip and gets a couple.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Fuller on off, Stokes defends it off the front foot.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Another one away from the off stumps, Stokes shows his awareness of his off stump and leaves it alone.
On the fourth stump line, Ben leaves it alone to get through the over.

NOT OUT! Umpire's call! West Indies do not lose their review but it is not good enough to overturn the decision. Good length delivery pitching outside off and jagging back in. Sibley looks to flick but misses and gets hit high on his pad. The West Indies player put in a hug appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Roach is confident and Holder goes with his bowler's instinct. Relay rolls in and Ultra Edge shows that there is no bat involved. Time for the Ball Tracker and it shows the Pitching is red, the Impact is red but the wicket is hitting on umpire's call. Sibley survives.
NO BALL! Roach oversteps. He bowls it outside off and Sibley leaves it.
Fuller on off, Sibley defends it off his front foot.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Outside off, Dom leaves it alone.
On the pads, Sibley flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Sibley looks to defend but the ball goes between the bat and pad.
Outside off, not played at.
One more delivery outside off, left alone again.
Attacks the stumps this time, Stokes gets right behind it and keeps it out.

That is a gem! Too good by Holder. He angles it into the off pole from around the wicket which means Stokes has to play at it. Gets it to pitch and then straighten. Squares Stokes up, luckily for the English batter, it beats his outside edge.
Goes back to leaving the ball does Stokes as it is bowled outside off again.
A harmless delivery to end the over! Outside off, not played at.
Length ball on off, Sibley defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Sibley has done this all day and looks like he can do it all week. He leaves it alone.
Outside off, Sibley does it again. He leaves it alone.
Closer to off pole, Sibley blocks it.
On the pads, Dom flicks it to the leg side and gets to the other end.
Length ball outside off, Stokes shows discipline and leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Sibley defends it with soft hands to the off side and takes a quick single. Good running this from the pair of Stokes and Sibley.
Full and angling in, the English all-rounder defends it.
Length ball on off, Stokes blocks it.
On off, Stokes blocks it.
Full and targeting the stumps, Stokes gets on his front foot and blocks it.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Down the leg side, Sibley looks to flick but misses. The ball keeps going away from Dowrich but he does well to dive and stop it.
On middle, Sibley turns it to the leg side and looks for a single but Stokes says no.
On the pads, Sibley flicks it to deep square leg and rotates the strike.
Beauty! Full outside off, the ball looks to be coming in but goes the other way off the deck. Stokes looks to defend but misses.
Full on the stumps, Stokes blocks it.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it alone. Another wicket-less over from Roach and his barren spell continues.
Full around off, Sibley defends it.
Outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to it.
Fuller on middle, Sibley pushes it towards mid on and gets a single.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Length ball outside off, Stokes looks to defend but the ball straightens and misses the outside edge. That will be Stumps on Day 1!
Starts off with a loosener, wide outside off, it is left alone.
Some movement again for Gabriel. He starts it from outside off though and gets it to shape away further. Left alone.
Outside off again, it is left alone again.
Finally bowls one on the stumps, this time there isn't any away movement, Sibley gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
BEATEN! A beauty. He makes this move away after landing it on off on a length. Sibley is half forward to defend but is beaten by the swing.

A dot to end! A much better start from Gabriel today. A tentative start from Sibley though. Gabriel bowls a full toss outside off. Sibley tried playing at it in a very unsure manner. He just hangs his bat out, in the end, he gets beaten.
On middle stump, Joseph starts nicely. Stokes gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
Two! First runs of the day! Fuller and around middle, Stokes plays it with a straight bat towards wide mid on. Gabriel is a touch slow in getting to the ball, two taken.
Gets it to swing into the left-hander again but this one is down the leg side. Left alone.
On the stumps, Stokes is solid in defense.

FOUR! Edgy but Stokes won't mind! This is angled away, on a fuller length from off. Stokes looks to push at it but does so inside the line. It goes off the outer half through backward point and races away to the fence. First one of the day.
A dot to end but a good over for England. Outside off, not played at.
A single to begin the over! Fuller and on middle, it is pushed towards mid on for one.
WIDE! That is very wide! It is the second slip fielder who caught the ball. The umpire had no hesitation to signal a wide.
Another one outside off, not as wide as the last one but still wide enough to not make the batter play.
One more ball well outside off, left alone.
4th delivery Stokes doesn't play at in this over since, it is bowled well outside off. Dowrich, like we saw yesterday, fails to collect the ball cleanly again. No runs taken though.
Finally makes the batter play by angling into the off pole, Stokes defends it.
Goes back to bowling well outside off, not played at.
Alzarri bowls it fuller outside off. The ball shapes away from the right-hander. Sibley watches it carry to the keeper.
Joseph bowls it closer to the off stump now and Sibley blocks it with a dead bat.
Good length delivery outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
Length ball on off, Sibley blocks it.
Down the leg side, Sibley looks to flick but misses.
Better length! Fuller and on off, Sibley defends it to get though the over.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it.
Ohh! That is a better line and length from Gabriel. Bowls it full and just outside off, the ball shapes away. Stokes leans forward to drive but misses it. Not far away from the edge.

Appeal but turned down. It is full and coming in. It is on the pads, Stokes looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pad. Half-hearted appeal from the West Indies player but turned down. Looked to be straying down leg and Hawk Eye confirms it.
Fuller on off, Stokes blocks it.
Down the leg side, Stokes looks to flick but misses.
On middle and leg, Stokes flicks it towards deep mid-wicket and keeps the strike.
On middle and off and coming in, Stokes pushes it with the swing towards mid on.
Fuller on off, once again Ben plays it with the swing to mid on.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Good length delivery away from the off pole, Stokes gets tempted to drive and has a go but the ball swings away and he misses.
On middle, played to mid on.
Good length ball pitching around off and going away. Stokes looks to defend but misses.
Wide outside off, Sibley leaves it.
Full on off, Sibley defends it.
Full on off, Sibley bends his back and blocks it.
Outside off and angling away. Sibley tries to have a feel of the ball but misses.
Gabriel finding his rhythm here. Bowls it on a length outside off and makes the ball jag back in. It does not come as much as Sibley predicted it to and ends up missing his defense.
Fuller on off, Sibley strokes it behind point and keeps the strike.
Shorter in length and on off, kept out.

Banana swing! A superb delivery but equally well played! This is angled into the middle pole, Joseph then gets it to move away beautifully. Sibley looks to play it with a straight bat, the another good thing he does is, he does not push hard at it and plays it with soft hands. It goes off the outside edge but well short of second slip. Good cricket all around.
Slightly shorter this time and around off, defended nicely.
Width on offer this time and it is short and outside off, Sibley pushes it through covers for two.

Fuller on middle, Stokes taps it towards mid on and takes a quick single to keep the strike.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Length ball pitching on middle, it jags back in. Stokes looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
FOUR! On the pads, Stokes is well set so he has no problem as he flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On off, defended by Stokes.
Full on off, Ben blocks it to get through the over.
On the pads, Sibley looks to flick but misses. The ball goes down the leg side off his thigh pad and they take a leg bye.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it.
Full outside off, Stokes shoulders arms to it.

Outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
On the pads, Sibley flicks it but finds mid-wicket.

Holder misses his line and sprays one down the leg side.Sibley does not bother playing that.

On off, Sibley blocks it.
Outside off and Sibley leaves it.

Stokes charges down the track and ends up yorking himself. Does well to jam it out.

Fuller on off, Stokes blocks it.
Full outside off, Stokes shows respect and leaves it alone.
Full on off, Stokes plays it to mid on and takes a quick single and keeps the strike.

EDGED AND FOUR! Good length delivery around off, it straightens up a bit. Stokes looks to turn it to the leg side but gets a leading edge which goes wide of gully and to the third man fence. 150-run stand comes up between the pair and Stokes with that edgy boundary moves to 80.
Good length ball outside off, Stokes looks to defend but the ball hits his bat behind his body.
This time defends astutely.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it.
On the pads, Stokes flicks it to the leg side and gets a single.
Down the leg side, Sibley leaves it alone.
Full outside off and shaping away. Stokes looks to defend but misses.

Mix up but safe! Good length ball around off, Stokes shuffles and plays it towards mid on. Stokes is desperate for a single and comes halfway down but Sibley sends him back. Ben is quick to turn his bike and get back in and also the fielder is a bit late to get to the ball.
On the pads, Stokes flicks it towards fine leg and gets three as the fielder cleans it up.

On the pads, Sibley tucks it to the leg side and gets to the other end.

Holder bangs it in short, Sibey gets on his back foot and pulls it towards square leg. The fielder from fine leg cleans it p before the ropes. Three taken.

The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Good length ball on off, Stokes blocks it.
On the pads, Ben looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Outside off left alone by the English all-rounder.
Full around off, Sibley flicks it to the right of fine leg and gets a couple.

Away from the off pole, Sibley shoulders arms to it.
On off, Sibley blocks it.
No run.
Outside off, Sibley has no business with it.
Down the leg side, Stokes  does not disturb that.

EDGED AND FOUR! Good length ball pitching on off, Stokes looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge which does not carry to the man at gully and goes wide of him for a boundary. Frustration for West Indies.
Now Ben defens it right off the meat of his bat.
Defended off the front foot by Ben Stokes presenting the full face of the bat.
FOUR! Beautiful from Ben Stokes. Moves into the 90s in style. Half volley around off from Alzarri. Stokes gets on his front foot and drives it exquisitely through mid off for a boundary.
On off defended by Stokes.
Outside off, left alone.
A couple! Full and on middle, Sibley works it through mid-wicket and takes two. 98 he moves onto.

On off, kept out nicely.
Outside off, left alone.

On middle, it is worked against the angle to mid-wicket.

Outside off, not played at.

Outside off, left alone. Joseph has just been warned for running onto the danger area. He was threatening to do so a lot of times yesterday and now has been officially warned.
A single to end as this is pushed towards cover.
Nasty! That took off from nowhere. Slightly shorter and on the body, it gets big on Stokes who looks to defend it by taking one hand off, the ball though hits his arm.
Shorter and way outside off, Stokes throws his bat at it but connects to thin air.
Another one banged in short. Stokes looks to pull but it comes off the upper half of his bat, hits his rub and then deflects to the leg side. They take a single.
Good length ball around off, Sibley blocks it.
Outside off, left alone by Sibley.
Outside off, Sibley is in no hurry to get to his century and leaves it alone.
On the pads, Stokes tucks it towards backward square leg and gets a single to move to 95.

HUNDRED FOR SIBLEY! His second in Tests and first in England. He is ecstatic as he pumps the air and removes his helmet as his teammates applaud him. It has been a calm, patient and an old school Test match innings from him but one which has been very valuable. Excellent composure shown by him and it has taken him 312 deliveries to reach his milestone. Full ball on off, Sibley drives it through mid off and gets three to reach to his second Test ton. 5th slowest century for England in Tests since 1990. Sibley hugs Stokes and it has been a fine knock. Unfortunately it is in a closed stadium but all the English fans would have enjoyed every part of it sitting at home.
On off, Stokes blocks it.
Length ball on off, Stokes looks to defend but gets an inside edge which rolls to the leg side off his body. He takes a single.
On off, pushed to mid off.
Back of a length delivery on off, Sibley hops and keeps it down.
Good delivery! Slightly shorter around off, it moves away a bit, squaring up Stokes.
Way outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Outside off, Stokes looks to punch it but does not get it off the middle. Missed opportunity as it was there for the taking.
On the pads, Stokes turns it to fine leg and takes a single. 3 away from a ton is the England Test vice captain.
Outside off and keeps swinging away. Dowrich dives almost to first slip and takes it.
Full and wide outside off, Sibley looks to play but misses.
Floated outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Shorter around off, Stokes tucks it to the leg side against the spin.
Flighted outside off, Stokes leaves it.
Stokes moves to 99! It is on the pads, Stokes flicks it towards backward square leg and gets a couple.
No hurry! Floated on off, Stokes blocks it.
Flighted outside off, Stokes looks to defend but misses. That is it from the morning session. Stokes will head to the break on 99. Lunch on Day 2!
Roach starts with a fuller delivery on middle and off, Sibley looks to flick but gets a leading edge towards point.
Good length ball outside off, Sibley leaves it alone. Inward movement once the  ball went past the stumps.
Fuller on the stumps, Sibley blocks it.
Down the leg side, Sibley looks to flick but misses.
Full and jagging back in from off, Sibley defends it with the swing towards mid-wicket.

Appeal for an LBW but the umpire is unmoved. Good length ball coming back in. Sibley looks to defend but misses and gets hit high on the thigh pad. The West Indies player are a bit keen but the umpire is not. Height seemed to be an issue. Holder opts against the review.
Floated outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Shorter on off, Stokes blocks it.

FOUR! HUNDRED FOR BEN STOKES! This has been a fine knock from the English all-rounder and he is rightly appreciated by his teammates. This hasn't been a typical Stokes innings but one with patience and calmness. His 10th Test hundred and his slowest century so far. He gets there in fine style. Flighted on middle and leg, Stokes gets in position and reverse sweeps it through backward point to bring up his ton.
Back to defending as he blocks this off the front foot.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it.
Tossed up outside off, Stokes shoulders arms to it.
Fuller and on off, it is driven through mid off for two.
Good length ball outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
A little too easy, it is worked through square leg for two.
Outside off, left alone.

NOT OUT! Clipping the top of middle! Umpire's call! It lands on middle and then straightens. Sibley looks to play across the line but fails to get bat on ball. He is hit high on the pads. An appeal but it is turned down. Holder reviews. Replay shows that the umpire's decision is the right one.
Played through mid-wicket by the batsman. The batsmen have run through for a single.
Darted around the pads. Sibley flicks it to short fine leg.
Shorter off spinner, Sibley goes on his back foot and blocks it.

On the pads, Sibley flicks it fine down the leg side and gets three. The fielder from short fine leg gives it a chase and stops it before the ropes. He slips and almost has his boot touch the rope but luckily it does not.
Flights one on off, Stokes keeps it out.
Once again Stokes continues to keep his calm and blocks it.
Flighted on off, BS defends it.
Outside off, left alone.
Length and around off, Sibley pushes at it tentatively, it goes off the outside edge but well short of Holder at second slip. He played it with soft hands.

NOT OUT! Holder probably should have not taken it after waiting for so long because it is missing leg. That ball did a little too much. Windies lose a review. This is fuller and around off, it tails back in. Sibley looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal but turned down. Review time. Replays roll in and they show the umpire is correct once again.
Outside off, Sibley guides this through backward point for two.
On the off pole, defended.
Outside off, not played at.
Off spinner outside off, Stokes looks to defend but misses.
On the pads, Stokes flicks it to mid-wicket for one.

FOUR! First aggressive shot from Sibley and that also brings up 200-run stand between Sibley and Stokes. Tossed up on middle and off, Sibley gets down on one knee and sweeps it with the spin towards square leg for a boundary.
On the pads, Sibley tucks it to short leg.
On the pads, Sibley flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, Sibley blocks it.
Sign of intent from Stokes! He takes a few steps down the track and makes this into a full ball. He hits it nicely but straight to mid on.

SIX! Nonchalant! Amazing! So Stokes has probably decided to step on the gas now and we could be in for some fun. Joseph though bowls it in his arc, full and on middle, Stokes just lifts it with utmost ease and lofts it over the wide long on fence.
Shorter and around off, kept out.
Good length ball around off, it is defended onto the ground.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
A single to end! On middle, it is worked towards mid-wicket for one.

On off, blocked.
Works this with the turn through square leg for one.

Flatter and quicker outside off, Stokes lets it be.
Another one on middle, Stokes is solid in defense.
Outside off, left alone.
Fires it on middle, it is kept out.
Worked with the turn through the leg side for one.
On the stumps, blocked.
Shorter and around off, Stokes pushes it towards cover for one.
Fires it on the stumps, it is kept out nicely.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
FOUR! Out comes the reverse sweep, Stokes innovates. Connects sweaty and hits it for a boundary in the third man region.
On middle, Stokes works it towards mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
On middle and leg, spinning further down the leg side. Sibley looks to flick but misses it.
Sibley walks down the track, he does not get to the pitch of it so pads it off.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Stokes comes down the track and shoulders arms to it. Dowrich looks to run him out but misses and also Stokes was in.
Good shot and good running. Length ball outside off, Stokes punches it through covers. The fielder in  the deep moves to his left. Stokes wants two and gets it with ease.
Full on off and middle, Stokes comes down the track and looks to flick but gets a leading edge which goes towards backward point for a single.

FOUR! Stokes getting into an aggressive mood here. It is on the pads, Stokes whips it with aggression through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Stokes charges down the ground and away from the stumps. Holder bowls it wide outside off.

Outside off, Stokes does not disturb that.

NOT OUT! Umpire's call it is and West Indies have retained their review but it is not good enough to change the on field umpire's call. Good length ball pitching on middle and off, it comes back in a bit. Stokes moves across and looks to flick but misses and gets hit high on the pads. West Indies players appeal but the umpire does not agree. Holder thinks and has a word with his teammates and then decides to signal the 'T'. The front foot is fine first up. Time for Ultra Edge and it shows no spike as the ball goes past the bat. Time for the Ball Tracker and it shows the Pitching is red. The Imapact is red but the Wicket is hitting on umpire's call.
On middle, it is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Fires it on middle, Stokes blocks it.
Shorter and around off, Stokes goes back and pushes it through covers for three.
On the pads, it is worked towards mid-wicket.
On the pads again, Sibley works it once again towards mid-wicket.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball. The batsmen have picked up a couple of runs.
NO BALL! Holder oversteps his line as he bowls this one full outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
FOUR! Full on middle, Stokes lofts it over mid on and fetches himself a boundary.
FOUR! Stokes in overdrive here. Overpitched on off, Stokes leans on his front foot and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Outside off, Stokes throws his bat and fails to connect.
On off, Stokes defends it with soft hands and takes a single.
On the stumps, Sibley blocks it.
Sibley blocks this one and gets through the over.
ON middle, it turns away. Stokes looks to defend but it goes off the outer half towards point for one.
It pitches outside off and then turns back in. Sibley looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads.
Floats it up on off, Sibley keeps it out nicely.
On middle, blocked nicely.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Down the leg side, it is left alone.

EDGED AND FOUR! It would have taken some catching. Full ball outside off, Stokes throws his bat at it but edges it. The ball goes over first slip.  Blackwood there jumps and gets his fingers on it but fails to get anything more and the ball races away to the fence.
Shorter on off, Stokes looks to pull but misses and gets hit on  the body.
FOUR! Beautiful shot from Stokes! Fuller on off and middle, Stokes lofts it with brilliant balance over mid on for a boundary.
Outside off, Stokes plays it to point and gets a couple to bring up his 150. This has been a fine knock from him and now he is looking to accelerate. Not a good sign for West Indies.
No ball! Gabriel oversteps. He bowls it full outside off, Stokes punches it to the off side and gets a single.
Outside off, Sibley looks to defend but misses.
Outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
On middle, it is kept out.
Shorter and outside off, Stokes slaps it through covers for a couple.
On the pads, it is worked towards square leg.
The batsman has driven it through mid on. One run added to the total.
The ball strikes the batsman very low on the pads

OUT! IN THE AIR... TAKEN! Stop the press, the partnership has finally been broken! Sibley's marathon knock has come to an end. It was needed to up the ante and Sibley tried doing so. He used his feet, looks to whip it over the mid-wicket fence but only manages a top edge. It balloons high up in the air towards Roach in the deep who runs to his left and takes a tumbling catch.
Full on off, Pope defends it towards gully.
On middle, Pope nudges it towards mid on and gets a single to get off the mark.
Full and wide outside off, Stokes shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, Ben leaves it alone.
Outside off and once again Ben is not interested.
Length ball closer to the off stumps, Stokes punches it towards cover-point and gets a single.
On middle, kept out.
Another one on the stumps, Stokes is solid in defense.
Shorter and outside off, Stokes cuts it through point for one.
Another one on middle, Pope keeps it out.

Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off again, left alone again.

DROPPED! Tough chance! Shorter and around off, Stokes looks to play the upper cut. It flies off the face towards gully who dives and looks to take it but spills it.

Shorter and outside off, Stokes looks to cut but gets a bottom edge.
The batsman gets to the pitch of the ball and defends it. One run added to the total.
Comes down the track and keeps it out.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.

OUT! LBW! That is plumb in front! Pope goes back for a low score. He misses a straight ball there. It is on middle, Pope goes back and looks to defend. He fails to put bat on ball and is struck on the pad. An appeal and up goes the finger.
Down the leg side, left alone.
Outside off, Stokes slams it to deep point for a single.
Full on middle, Buttler flicks it to mid on.
Full on off, Jos blocks.
Outside off, Buttlr shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.

NOT OUT! West Indies lose all their reviews. The ball is doing too much and it is missing leg. Good length ball pitching on middle and coming back in. Buttler looks to defend but misses and gets ht on the pad. West Indies player put in a huge appeal but it falls into deaf ears. Holder thinks about it and decides to refer it. Replay rolls in and after a few views and angles the umpire decides that Gabriel's front foot is fine. Time for the Ultra Edge which shows no bat. Ball Tracker then comes on and it shows the Pitching is in line, the Impact is line but the ball is going to miss the stumps. Buttler survives and misery piles on the tourists as they have lost all their reviews.
On middle, kept out.
BEATEN! Big turn. This lands on middle, it pitches and spins away. Stokes looks to defend but is beaten.
Flatter and on middle, it is kept out.
Shorter and outside off, Stokes guides it through point for one.
Quicker and on middle, Buttler keeps it out.
A single as this is worked down to fine leg.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.
Outside off, left alone.
One more delivery outside off, not played at.
On middle, it is worked towards the bowler.
Outside off, it is not played at.
Full and on the pads, Stokes looks to flick but misses. An appeal but turned down. Going down leg.
Works it with the turn towards mid-wicket.
On middle, kept out.
FOUR! Short and wide, asking to be hit. Buttler stays back and smashes it through covers for a boundary. This is a good chance for Buttler to find some form with the bat.
Shorter in length and outside off, Buttler pushes it through covers for two now.
On the pads, worked to mid-wicket.
That ball has struck the batsman on the thigh-pad.
Shorter and on middle, it is pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off, not played at.
On the pads, it is worked through mid-wicket for two.

EDGED BUT SHORT! Wouldn't have mattered though as it was a NO BALL! Length and around off, it pitches and shapes away. Stokes looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge and lands short of Holder.
A push towards mid off for one.
Fuller and on off, Buttler strokes it towards mid off.
On middle, kept out.
On middle, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Delicate! On the pads, it is worked down to fine leg for a boundary.
Wide outside off stump, the batsman leaves it alone.

The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On middle, defended.

A huge shout but nothing from the umpire! Looked really close! Smart from Chase. He bowls the straighter one this time. It lands on off and straightens just a touch. Enough to save Stokes who leaves it and is hit on the pads. Chase can't believe that isn't given but Hawk Eye shows it is the right call.
On middle, kept out.

A dot to end as this is fired on the stumps. Buttler keeps it out. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 2!
Fires it on middle, this is eased down to long on for one.
On off, shorter, it turns into the batter sharply. Buttler gets hit on the thigh pad.
Slower through the air around off, Buttler looks to defend but it turns in, it goes off the inner half through square leg for one.
Outside off, left alone.
Out comes the reverse sweep but straight towards backward point. The fielder can't stop a run.
Loopy ball on off, it is pushed back to the bowler.
Stokes uses his feet straightaway to the pacer and slaps the ball through covers but only for one.
Shorter and outside off, Buttler looks to drag the pull but misses.

Down the leg side, Buttler looks to play it fine but misses.

FOUR! Reverse swept brilliantly! Buttler knows there is no one at point so he plays it through there and bags a boundary.

Quicker and outside off, Buttler looks to cut but misses.

FOUR! Another juicy full toss and Buttler says thank you very much. He creams it through covers for the third boundary in the over. A very good over for England.
On off, it is kept out.

OUT! TAKEN! Roach finally, finally gets a wicket. He has had to wait for more than 4 innings to do so. He deserves it. He has been continuously running in, giving it his all with a smile, this should make him feel a lot better. He bowls this one outside off and it is on a length. Stokes looks to play the reverse sweep but the ball kisses the glove and goes to the keeper. An appeal and up goes the finger. End of a superb innings from Stokes. He misses out on a double ton but we are pretty sure that wasn't on his mind.

OUT! Caught! Two-in-two for Roach. One brings two and that is exactly the case for Kemar. This is a length delivery around off, Woakes pushes at it but the ball shapes away a touch. Goes off the outside edge towards gully where Hope takes a good low catch. Not a good return into the side with the bat for Woakes.
Not a good hat-trick ball! It is outside off, easy leave for Curran.
This is a top nut! Not sure how that missed the off pole. It lands just outside off and cuts back in. Goes between the pad and the bat of Curran who looks to defend and over the off pole.
A harmless delivery to end a double-wicket over. Outside off, left alone.
Down the leg side, it is left alone.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg.

The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Shorter and outside off, this one takes off after pitching. Curran looks to cut but ends up underedging it.
On middle, it is played right back to the bowler.
On the stumps again, Curran keeps it out. Two maidens in a row.
Full on off, Buttler defends it off his front foot.
Outside off, Buttler is hapy to watch it carry to the keeper.
Full on the pads, Buttler flicks it to the right of mid-wicket. Blackwood there dives and saves runs for his side. Good commitment from the West Indian JB .
Length ball on off, Buttler tucks it to short mid-wicket.
Outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.
Good length delivery outside off, Jos knows where his stumps are and does not disturb this one.
Shorter and outside off, it is mistimed towards cover.
Works it with the angle towards mid-wicket for one.

SIX! Enough of blocking says Curran. He plants his front foot forward and hacks it against the turn but with the angle. Over the long on fence for a biggie.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
A single to end as this is worked through square leg for one.
Shorter and well wide outside off, Curran looks to cut but misses by a long way.

Back of a length and on off, defended.
A quick run! Shorter and outsi9de off, Curran looks to defend it away from the body. It goes off the inner half towards the leg side for one.
On off, kept out.
Shorter on off, Curran tucks it to mid-wicket.
Flighted on off, Curran blocks it.
Flighted on off, Curran strokes it to mid on for one.

Floated on off, Buttler pushes it towards mid off and rotates the strike.

FOUR! Lovely from Curran! He has probably decided to take on the spinner. Chase fires it on the pads, Curran goes down on one knee and sweeps it through backward square leg. There is a fielder in the deep but he has no chance.
Full and on middle, this is hit down to long on for one.
Full outside off, Curran plays it to mid off who is standing at the edge of the circle which allows Curran to take a single.
Beaten! Good length ball outside off, Buttler looks to defend but misses.

OUT! CAUGHT! Buttler holes out! Trying to take on the West Indies skipper, Buttler goes for a big hit but unsuccessfully. Fuller ball on middle and leg, Buttler flicks it uppishly. He gets the height but not enough distance. It goes to the left of deep square leg. Alzarri Joseph there seems to have misread it but manages to take the catch.
Fuller around off, Curran pushes it towards cover and takes a run.
Outside off, Bess looks to defend but misses.
On off, Curran defends it.
Shorter on off, Curran defends it off his back foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! 5-wicket haul for Chase and he has been the ray of shining hope in this innngs for the tourists. He will be a happy man and England now 9 down. Floated on middle and off, Curran looks to reverse sweep it but gets no timing and serves a dolly at point. Kraigg Brathwaite there takes a simple catch.
Floated on off, Broad blocks it.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On off, road manages to see it off.
Very full and shaping away! Bess looks to jam it out but it goes off the outside edge towards gully who makes a good diving stop.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
On off, it is defended nicely.
Fuller and on middle, Bess keeps it out.
Good length and on off, defended nicely.
On a good length and around off, it is defended nicely.
FOUR! Bonus runs these. Flighted on the pads, Broad gets down on one knee and sweeps it through backward square leg for a boundary.
Floated on off, Broad defends it.
Floated on off, Broad plays it to point for a run.
Short outside off, Bess cuts it behind square on the off side and gets a run.
On the pads, Broad paddles it down the leg side and gets a couple.
Flighted outside off, Broad looks to defend but misses.

Edged but safe! Gabriel bowls a pacy ball on a length. It is on off, Bess looks to turn it to the leg side but gets a leading edge which flies over  point and towards third man. There is no one there so they take two.
Fuller on off, Bess plays it through covers and gets a couple.
On off, Bess blocks it.

Gabriel has missed the chance to call curtains on this innngs. Tiredness maybe the issue. Back of a length ball on off, Bess pulls it to the left of deep mid-wicket and calls for two. Broad hesitates but decides to put his head down and go for the second. The throw is towards Gabriel who is at the bowler's end and Broad is short. The throw is a bit away from the stump and Shannon decides to throw it rather than run to the stumps. He misses and the innings continues.
FOUR! This will rub salt on Gabriel's wound. On the pads, Bess flicks it fine down the leg side and gets a boundary.

DROPPED AND SIX! Roach puts down Bess in the deep and to makes matters worse it has touched the ropes on the full. Floated on middle, Bess goes over mid-wicket. It goes straight towards deep mid-wicket. Roach there does not have to move an inch but the ball hits his fingers and hits the ropes for a biggie.
Short on off, Bess pulls it to mid-wicket but with no timing.
Flighted outside off, Bess looks to defend but the ball hits him on the pads and goes to first slip.
FOUR! On the pads, Bess sits down and sweeps it through deep square leg. Roach gives it a chase and dives but to no avail.
On the pads, Bess turns it to mid-wicket and takes a single. That will be it as Root has had enough and calls the batters. England declare at 469/9.
Starts off with a delivery outside off, it is left alone.
Windies are off the mark! It is on the pads, it is worked towards square leg for one.
Campbell is off the mark now as he too gets one on the pads, works it towards fine leg for one.
Well bowled! Lands it around off, gets it to straighten a touch. Brathwaite tries to defend but it goes off the outer half towards cover.

A huge shout but it has been turned down. Broad was pretty excited. It is a length delivery outside off, it comes back in a touch.Brathwaite looks to play it with a straight bat but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Broad, Root and Buttler have a discussion but then don't review. Rightly so as Hawk Eye shows the impact to be outside off.
A dot to end as the last ball is pushed towards cover.
Good length and on off, kept out.
Length delivery, angling away from off. Left alone.
One more length ball outside off, left alone. No movement for Woakes so far.
Fuller this time but once again not a lot of movement, it is driven towards mid off.
Lands it outside off, not played at.
A little too straight, Campbell looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. A harmless maiden from Woakes.
Attacks the stumps, kept out.
Outside off, left alone.
Good movement! Length and around off, it shapes away after pitching. Brathwaite initially looks to poke at it but then bails out.

Good delivery! This starts around middle and then keeps slanting away with the angle. Campbell is drawn into playing at it but due to the angle away, he gets beaten.

Well played in the end! This is shorter and it sticks in the surface. Campbell is committed to the shot a touch early. He though does well to take one hand off the handle and keep it along the ground.
A single now as this is worked down towards fine leg. Had to put bat to ball there or he would have been an LBW candidate.
A little too straight. Campbell looks to flick but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
BEATEN! Broad is so good to the left-handers. Comes from around the wicket, angles it into the batter, he gets it to leave him after pitching. Campbell is beaten as he tries to defend.
Just outside off, Campbell watches it and lets it be.
FOUR! First real poor ball by Broad and Campbell puts it away. Full and angled into the pads, the batter clips it in style through mid-wicket for a boundary. First of the innings.
On middle, defended solidly.
Outside off again, left alone.
One more ball outside off, Brathwaite shoulders arms to this one.
On the stumps, kept out.
One more delivery outside off, left alone again.
The batsman tries flicking a ball that is down the leg side.
On middle, Campbell keeps it out nicely.
On a good length and around off, defended nicely.
Well played! Length and around off, it skids through. Campbell gets his bat down in time and keeps it out.
FOUR! Sweet is how that can be defined! Fuller and around off, Campbell leans into it and creams it through mid off for a boundary. The Windies batters have started off well here.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.

How has Campbell got bat on that one? That has not bounced at all. It is on a length and around middle, stays low. Campbell gets his bat down in time and it goes towards fine leg. Broad appeals thinking it is pad first but the umpire shakes his head.
Outside off, Campbell leaves it.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, defended nicely.
Back of a length and on off, this is guided to point.
Played to the point region by the batsman.
Outside off, not played at.
On a length on off, Brathwaite plays it to covers.
Length delivery on middle, Brathwaite flicks it to mid-wicket.

On a good length on off, Kraigg defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Brathwaite keeps it out.
On a good length on off, Campbell plays it to point.
Good length delivery outside off, John leaves it alone.
On a good length on off, Campbell blocks it off the front foot.

OUT! THREE REDS! Campbell is a goner! An excellent bowling change from Root! Curran has this habit of picking up a wicket when his team needs it. Just 4 balls into his first over and he gets rid of one opener. Excellent review too! Curran bowls it full and around off, it shapes in a touch. He got this one to come in after taking the last two away. Campbell looks to drive but there are two noises. It has hit the pad for sure but is it bat-pad or pad and pad? England appeal and the umpire feels its the former and shakes his head. England review. Replays show it is front pad and back pad. Time for the Hawk Eye and it shows the on-field call has to be overturned. Another low score for Campbell, England would like one more before Stumps.
Fuller and on middle, driven to mid off.
Outside off, left alone. End of a successful over by Curran.
Tossed up delivery on off, Brathwaite plays it towards mid off.
Floated delivery on middle, Brathwaite drives it towards mid on.
Loopy delivery on off, Brathwaite drives it towards mid off.
On middle, Brathwaite flicks it through square leg for a run.
Flighted delivery on off, Joseph looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man. The batsmen get two runs.
On off, Joseph drives it through covers. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get three runs.
On a length on middle, Joseph flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen get two runs.
Good length delivery outside off, Joseph shoulders arms to this one.
Length delivery on leg, Joseph flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
On a good length on off, Brathwaite blocks it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Kraigg keeps it out.
On a length on middle, Brathwaite flicks it towards the leg side.
Tossed up delivery on off, Joseph drives it back towards the bowler.

Floated delivery on off, Joseph defends it out.
Full delivery on off, Joseph lofts it over covers. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get two runs.

On a length on middle, Brathwaite plays it towards mid on and takes a quick single.
On a good length on off, Joseph defends it out.
Good length delivery on off, Joseph blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Curran bowls a bouncer, Joseph looks to pull but it goes off the top edge. It goes over the keeper towards fine leg for a boundary.

Howzattttt? The umpire shakes his head! Curran really likes it. He has a word with his skipper about a review but Root does not. Coming to the ball. It is a full one, excellent from Curran follows the short one with a really full one which tails back in from outside off. Joseph looks to jam it out but there are two noises. Curran appeals feeling it brushed the pad first but the umpire shakes his head. England do not review but... replays just show that it brushed the pad first. Maybe if it had been a top order player, they would have probably gone for it but since it was Joseph, they might have decided against. All Curran can do now is smile.
On a good length on off, Alzarri keeps it out. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2!
