Starts off with a very full delivery, looking for some swing but there ain't any. Ends up sliding it on the pads, Brathwaite finds the fielder at square leg as he flicks it.
A little too straight again, Brathwaite works it to that fielder once again. This time though, he needed to dive to his left and stop it.
Shortens his length slightly and bowls it on off, Kraigg goes back and keeps it out.
BEATEN! First sign of any movement today. It is off the pitch. It lands on off and on a length. Straightens after pitching. Brathwaite is squared up as he tries to block. Gets beaten.
Back of a length and on off, Kraigg stays back and keeps it out.
Outside off, left alone. A maiden to begin with by Woakes.
First run today! This is shorter and around off, Joseph plays it late, guides it through backward point for one.
Outside off, Brathwaite covers his off pole and lets it be.
Wider outside off, Brathwaite does not play at it again.
Even wider this time, outside off. It swings away further. Buttler dives to his right but only gets a hand to it. It goes towards third man for one. Wide signaled too. Wayward from Broad there.
Gets it right now, bowls it on off and on a length. Defended.
On the pads, Joseph works it towards square leg and gets to the other end.
A dot to end! On off, defended solidly.
Leading edge but three runs! This is angled into the pads, Joseph closes the face of the bat a little too early as he tries to flick. It goes off the leading edge through backward point for three.

Another edge but once again runs for the batter! This is a good delivery, it lands on middle and then straightens. Brathwaite looks to defend but it goes off the outer half through backward point again for three.
On off, defended nicely. AJ is doing a good job till now.

DROPPED! Just as we praised Joseph, he offers a chance but it has been put down by Stokes. Maybe he was put off by Crawley who dived to his left from third slip. However, this will frustrate the English even more. They need to hang on to every opportunity they get. Woakes bowls it on a back of a length and just outside off. Joseph pushes at it tentatively. It goes to the right of Stokes at second slip. Crawley goes for it initially with a dive but then bails out. Stokes it caught by surprise. He tries to react quickly but the ball bursts through his hands and goes towards third man for one.
A similar delivery to the last one, Brathwaite though goes back, watches it nicely and guides it through point for a couple.

FOUR! Nice and fine! Down the leg side, Brathwaite loves it there, he works it very fine and it races towards the fine leg fence. End of what could have been a successful over for England, ends up being a good one for the Windies.
Outside off, left alone.
On a length and around off, Joseph keeps it out.
On the stumps again, AJ keeps it out with ease.
A sharp bumper, on middle, Joseph is late in the pull. He gets a top edge towards square leg. A single taken. 50-up for West Indies, still trailing by 419 runs.
OHHH! Close! Broad goes wide of the crease and angles it on off, Brathwaite looks to defend but the ball moves away and goes past the outside edge. Not a lot you can do about that delivery.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Another tentative push from Joseph. This time though he does not edge it. Shorter and outside off, moves away ever so slightly. Joseph hangs his bat out but luckily he gets beaten.
Gets this one to come back in a little, the length though is shorter. Joseph looks to flick but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.

A run out chance! What was Joseph doing there? He just pushes this length ball towards mid off and takes off. Halfway down he probably realizes there is no run and also, sees Brathwaite not coming. He turns and tries to make it back. The fielder picks the ball up and has a shy at the keeper's end but misses. A direct hit and Joseph was a goner.
Good length and on off, Joseph keeps it out.
Another good length delivery on middle, Joseph keeps it out.
The batsman tries flicking a ball that is down the leg side.
Angled into the pads, Brathwaite works it towards the leg side for a couple.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman. One run added to the total.

FOUR! Just a push and Joseph bags a boundary! This is on a length and around off, AJ just uses the pace, opens the face of the bat slightly and it races away to the point boundary. These are frustrating runs for England.

EDGY FOUR! More frustration for the hosts! Broad bowls a length delivery around off, Joseph pushes at it with hard hands. It goes between third slip and gully and to the third man fence. Consecutive boundaries for the visitors.
A couple now! This is a lovely stroke! It is on the up. Length and around off, Joseph stands tall and pushes it through mid off and takes an easy two.

FOUR LEG BYES! This was bowled in frustration. A quick bumper, Joseph is way too late in the pull. It hits his shoulder and goes over the slip cordon for a boundary. An excellent over for the Windies. The 50-run stand is also up, handy, handy partnership for the visitors. They trail by another 402 runs.
Good length and on off, kept out.
Outside off, not played at.
BEATEN! Nice swinging delivery. It starts on off and then tends to move away. Brathwaite looks to defend but is beaten by the movement.
One more ball outside off, Brathwaite initially hangs his bat out but then bails away.
Outside off, left alone.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Fuller and it shapes back in a touch. Joseph looks to drive but it goes off the inner half towards square leg.
Drags his length back a little and on off, defended nicely.
Fuller again and on middle, Joseph drives it nicely but to mid on.
Outside off, Joseph lets it be.
A surprise bumper, Joseph ducks under it nicely.
A solid defense to end. On off, blocked.
A little too straight, it is worked towards square leg for one.
Outside off, not played at.
On the pads, Joseph looks to flick but misses. It brushes the pads and goes to the keeper.
A bumper, Joseph ducks under it.
Outside off, left alone.
Good shot and good stop! Fuller and on middle, Joseph strokes it back towards the bowler who dives to his right and stops it brilliantly.
BEATEN! Excellent use of the angle there. He lands it on off, Curran generally gets the ball into the batter but gets it to leave him this time. Brathwaite is beaten as he tries to defend.
On the pads, it is worked towards the leg side for one.
On off, it is pushed towards cover for one.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, defended nicely.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Floated on off, Joseph blocks it.

OUT! CAUGHT! Bess comes and makes an impact straightaway. The night watchman who was technically not out for a whole day has to go. Quicker off spinner on middle and leg, Joseph looks to defend but it goes off the inner half of the bat uppishly to the right of short leg. Pope there shows great reflexes and takes a very good catch. Alzarri's inning comes to an end and England finally have a breakthrough.
Tossed up on middle and off, Hope starts his innings with a solid front foot defense.
Flighted on the stumps, Hope blocks.
Floated on the pads, Hope glances it on a bounce to the left of leg slip.
Beauty to end the over! Bess gives this air outside off, Hope lunges forward and looks to defend but the ball goes right between the bat and pad and misses the off pole by a whisker.
Good length ball on off, Kraigg blocks it.
On the pads, Brathwaite flicks it towards backward square leg for one.
Fuller on middle and leg, Hope blocks it towards mid on.
On off, Shai defends it.
Length delivery on the stumps, Shai defends it.
Good length ball on off, Hope pushes it towards cover but straight to the fielder.
Tossed up on middle, it is driven back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on off, Brathwaite keeps it out.
A little too full outside off, KB strokes it against the turn, through the gap at covers for two.
Floats it up on off, Brathwaite lunges forward and keeps it out.
Loopy ball and on middle, Brathwaite stays back and keeps it out.
One more delivery which is quicker and on off, Brathwaite goes back again to block it.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Yes, it is a half volley but it still has to be put away. Curran bowls it full and wide outside off. Hope goes down on one knee and caresses it through covers. No stopping that.
Good length and on off, Hope is solid in defense.
Fuller and on middle, Hope works it towards mid on.
Another full delivery, there is no swing for Curran. Hope strokes it back nicely towards the left of the bowler who gets down quickly, stops the ball and then has a shy at the striker's end.

FOUR! Take that, says Hope! Caresses once again. He loves playing the cover drive and he does so extremely stylishly. Full and wide outside off, Hope once again goes down on one knee and creams it through covers. Exceptional.
Hope misses out there! This is down the leg side, Hope looks to flick but fails to get bat on ball. A good over for the visitors.
Flighted on off, Brathwaite dabs it away from short leg.
Floated on off, Brathwaite tucks it with the spin in front of short leg.
On the pads, Brathwaite flicks it to the on side.
On the stumps, KB blocks it.
Tossed up on off, Brathwaite defends it off his front foot.
On the pads, Brathwaite flicks it to the leg side.
On the pads, Hope tucks it to the leg side.
Fuller on off and middle, Hope defends it to mid on.
Full on middle and off, Hope flicks it through mid-wicket and gets a couple.
On off, Hope blocks it.
Length ball around off and middle, Hop gets on his back foot and blocks it.
Full on middle and off, Hope flicks it through mid-wicket and gets a couple.
Floated on off, Brathwaite defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on middle, Brathwaite defends it.
On middle, Brathwaite plays it to mid on.
Flighted on off, Brathwaite taps it onto the ground.
On the pads, KB tucks it to the leg side.
On the stumps, kept out by Kraigg.
Good length ball on off, Hope defends it with a dead bat.
On middle, Hope defends it.
Fuller on off, SH defends it.
Good length ball on off, Hope blocks it.
Fuller on off, Shai pushes it to mid off.
Outside off, Hope leaves it in Steve Smith style.
Shorter on off and spinning in, Brathwaite dabs it in front of short leg.
Outside off, Brathwaite guides it behind point for one.
FOUR! Good shot! Floated full outside off, asking Hope to drive. He obliges and does so beautifully through covers and gets a boundary.
Darted on off, Hope blocks it.
Flighted outside off, Hope again goes for the drive but this time the ball spins and takes the inner half of his bat and goes towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, Hop lunges forward and blocks it.
On the pads, Brathwaite looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
On the body, Brathwaite tucks it to backward square leg.
Again on the body, KB tucks it to backward square leg.
This time the ball is on middle and Kraigg flicks it to mid-wicket.
Length delivery around off, Brathwaite defends it and shouts an audible no to his partner.
Broad extracts some bounce as he hits it a bit shorter. Brathwaite defends it with soft hands as the ball takes outer half of his bat and goes to gully along the ground.
Fighted on off, Hope defends it.
Shorter on off, Hope blocks it.
FOUR! Hammered away! Short on middle and leg, Hope gets on his back foot and hammers his pull with the spin through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On middle and fuller, Shai defends it.
Flighted outside off, Hope gets behind the ball and blocks it.
Floated around off, Hope pushes it to mid off.
On off, Brathwaite tucks it to the leg side.
Fuller around off, Brathwaite defends it.
On middle and leg, Brathwaits glances it to mid-wicket.
Short ball, Brathwaite sways away.
Outside off, Brathwaite guides it behind square on the off side. A lot of runs have coe there today and three more comes from that area.
Good length ball around off, Hope gets on his front foot and blocks it.
On the pads, Brathwaite looks to flick but misses. The ball goes down the leg side off his thigh pads and gets a couple.

NOT OUT! England lost their review! No bat at all on this one. On the pads,  Brathwaite looks to flick but the ball clips something as there is some noise and goes to Buttler. The English players appeal but the umpire turns it down. Root and Woakes have a word and the skipper decides to signal the 'T'. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge shows no spike as the ball goes past the bat. Brathwaite's fight continues.
FOUR! Short, wide and punished. Woakes is guilty of giving width outside off, Brathwaite is quick to pounce on it and cut it through point for a boundary.
FOUR! Once again similiar delivery and the same outcome. Outside off, Brathwaite frees his arms and slashes it through cover-point for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Away from the stumps, KB doesn't want to play that.
On the pads, flicked to the on side by Hope.
Short on middle, Hope dabs it to the on side.
Tossed up on middle, Hope strokes it to mid on.
Short and spinning in, Hope manages to keep his tuck away from short leg. Pope dives but to no avail.
Flighted outside off, Hope gets behind it and blocks it.
FOUR! Tossed up on middle and leg, Hope gets down on one knee and sweeps it perfectly wide of backward square leg for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle and off, Brathwaite tucks it toward mid-wicket and calls for a quick single.
Outside off, Brathwaite leaves it alone.
Outside off, Hope looks to defend but misses.
On off, Hope blocks it.
Length ball on off, Hope looks to defend but the ball shapes away a bit. It goes off the outside edge towards gully on a bounce.
Outside off, Shai watches it carry to Buttler.
Floated around off, Brathwaite gets on his front foot and drives it through covers. Broad gives it a chase and stops it before the ropes. Three taken by the batters.
On the pads, Hope flicks it to the on side.
Shorter on off, SH defends it.
On the leg side, Hope looks to flick but misses. There is a huge appeal but tuned down by the umpire. Replay shows it kissed the thigh pad not the bat.
Shorter on the leg side, Hope looks to pull but misses and gets hit on the body.
On off, Hope blocks it.
Good length and on off, defended.
Down the leg side, Brathwaite looks to flick but misses.
A huge shout but nothing! Angled into the pads, Brathwaite looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad. An appeal but turned down.
On the stumps, blocked.
This is angled into the pads, it is worked through mid-wicket for two.
Good length and on off, it is kept out.
Floated on off, Brathwaite lunges and looks to defend off his front foot but does so off the outer half of the bat.
Shorter on off, Hope blocks it off his back foot.
On off, Hop blocks it.
On the pads, Hope flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
On off, KB defends it.
Flighted on off, Brathwaite defends it.
On the pads, Hope blocks it.
Floated on middle, Hope pushes it to mid on.
On the pads, Hope flicks it to the leg side.
Flighted on off, Hope blocks it.
Tossed up on off, Shai defends it.
Flighted on off, Hope gets on his front foot and dabs the ball down the ground. Its Lunch on Day 4!
Curran starts with a fuller delivery on the stumps, Brathwaite gets bat on ball as he defends it.
Frst runs of the session. On the pads, Brathwaite flicks it to the on side and gets a single.
Length ball on top of middle, Hope defends it.
On the fourth stump line, Hope leaves it alone.
On middle and leg, Hope glances it to the leg side.
Fuller on off, Hope defends it with a dead bat to negate the first over of the post Lunch session.
Full outside off, Brathwaite pushes it to cover.

FOUR! Lovely shot! Broad overpitches it slightly on middle and off, Brathwaite keeps his balance and plays a delightful on-drive through mid on and gets a boundary. It also brings the 50-run stand between the two batters.
On the pads, KB flicks it and finds mid-wicket.
Outside off, Brathwaite leaves it alone.
On off, Brathwaite blocks it.
Fuller on off, KB keeps it out.
Fuller on off, Shai defends it.
On the stumps, Hope keeps it out.
Hope showing some Steve Smith technique as he leaves this ball which is way outside off alone.

OUT! Caught! Shai Hope departs and England have started the new session the way they would have been hoping for. Just the third over into the new session and Sam Curran has got rid of Shai Hope. Good bowling from the young English all-rounder. He has a knack of picking wickets and he has done just that. Good length ball just outside off, Hope gets on his front foot and looks to defend but the ball straightens and kisses the outside edge of the bat and goes straight to Jos Buttler behind the stumps. He takes an easy catch and the budding stand is broken.
Brooks starts his innings with a leave to the ball outside off.
Once again outside off, Brooks lets it carry to the keeper. End of a very successful over.

NOT OUT! Umpire's call on impact and Brathwaite survives by a whisker. Fuller delivery pitching outside off and jagging back in. Brathwaite gets on his front foot and looks to defend. He misses and gets hit on the front pad. There is a huge appeal for LBW, Broad cries for it but the umpire turns it down. Root decides to take it upstairs after a word with Broad. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge confirms that there is no bat involved. Time for Ball Tracker and it shows  that the Impact is the nly issue as it is yellow, meaning umpire's call. Brathwaite survives.
Outside off, Kraigg looks to defend but misses.

Too high! Good length ball pitching around off and coming back in. Brathwaite looks to defend but misses. Broad and his teammates appeal but the umpire says no. Broad looks at Root but Stokes from second slip says too high and he is right as it is confirmed by Ball Tracker.

FOUR! Fifty for Brathwaite. He has been very good so far but has to carry on. Excellent shot but Broad won't mind it. Full and angling in from off, Brathwaite keeps his balance and drives it through mid on for a boundary.
FOUR! Once again it is Brathwate who is getting the rewards. Full on middle, Brathwaite once again drives it through mid on and gets a boundary.
Outside off, KB lets it go.
On off, Brooks blocks it.
FOUR! Brooks is off the mark. On the pads, Brooks flicks it through suare leg and gets a boundary to get his scoreboard up and running.
Outside off, Brooks leaves it.
Length ball on off, Shamrah defends it.
Length ball on off, Brooks blocks it from within the crease.
On the stumps, Shamrah defends it to get through the over.
On the pads, Brathwaite flicks it through mid-wicket and gets a single.
On the fourth stump line, Brooks leaves it alone.
FOUR! Bad ball and punished. Broad strays on the pads, Brooks says thank you very much and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Outside off, left without teasing.
Again tempting Brooks to poke at the ball outside off, he is happy to let it carry to Buttler.
Closer to the off pole, Brooks blocks.
On the pads, Brathwaite turns it towards fine leg and gets to the other end.
Fuller around off, Brooks pushes it to cover.
On the pads, Brooks tucks it to mid-wicket.
Fuller on middle, Brooks gets on his front foot and keeps it out.
Back of a length on off, Brooks taps it to point.
On the pads, Brooks flicks it but finds mid-wicket.

EDGED AND FOUR! Lucky escape for Brathwait. Good length ball outside off, it pitches and straightens. Brathwaite looks to play it horizontally through point but gets a thick outside edge which goes through the gap between gully and second slip. Crawley there dives but to no avail.
On the pads, Brathwaite finds mid-wicket.
Fuller on off, Brathwaite defends it off the front foot.
Around off, played to point.
Driven through mid on by the batsman.
On the pads, Brathwaite flicks it to the on side.
Back of a length and on off, it is defended.
A little too straight, this is worked off the pads for two.
On off, defended nicely.
Good use of the angle! This is around off and angling away. Brooks looks to defend but is beaten.
Length and around off, it is pushed towards cover.
EDGY FOUR! Fuller and around off, the batter looks to drive but it goes off the outside edge towards the third man fence.
Length ball on off, Brathwaite defends it.
Bouncer! Brathwaite looks to pull but misses.
On the pads, Brathwaite flicks it to the leg side.
On off, Brathwaite blocks it.
Around off, Kraigg keeps it out.
Length ball on off, Brathwaite defends it.
Floated on off, Brooks blocks it.
FOUR! Bess gives it too much air and overpitches it on off, Bess gets on his front foot and drives it through point for a boundary.
Floated on off, Brooks blocks it.
Floated on off, Brooks squeezes it behind point and gets one.
Floated on off, Brathwaite blocks it.
Shorter outside off, Kraigg runs it down to third man and gets a couple.

Appeal for LBW but not out says the umpire. Looked really high and hence England do not take the review. A shortish ball angled into the batsman. Brooks looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads. A loud appeal follows but not out says the umpire.
Good length ball around off, blocked off the back foot.
Full and on off, Brooks pushes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Brooks has been targeting this fuller balls. He whips this one through mid-wicket for another boundary. He hit it with lot of power.
A quick single as Brooks tucks it shortish ball towards the right side of the man at mid on.
Shortish and around off, Brathwaite hops and blocks it off his back foot.
Floated around off and middle, Brooks blocks it nicely.
Full around off, this one is timed towards mid on.
Full again and around off, pushed back to the bowler by Brooks.
FOUR! Drilled through the covers. Runs are flowing for Brooks. Bess again bowls it full but this one is outside off. Brooks leans into the shot and slams it through the covers.

Three now as Bess bowls another full ball outside off. Brooks opens the face of the bat and guides it towards deep point. Three taken before the fielder can get to the ball. West Indies need 100 more to avo
Another full ball, Brathwaite calmly pushes it back to Bess.
Bouncer down the leg side. Brooks easily ducks under it.
Another bouncer but this one did not rise enough and hits Brooks on the back of his helmet.
NO BALL! Shortish and around off, Brooks forces it towards point. Stokes oversteps.
Short again and outside off, once again pushed towards point.
Down the leg side this time. Brooks lets it be.
Stokes is targeting the body as he bends his back and bowls it short around the body. Brooks tucks it towards fine leg for a run.
Shortish and around off, Brathwaite works it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Full and around off, Brathwaite strokes it towards cover.
Full and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Just around off on a fuller length. Brathwaite comes forward and defend it.
Quicker one around off and middle, Brathwaite stays on the back foot to block it.
Too full and outside off, Brathwaite goes for the drive but doesn't time it well but good enough for two.
Short and on the pads, Brathwaite fails to pull this time and ends up finding square leg.
Good bumper from Stokes. Brooks does well to duck under it. Stokes has overstepped again. He will have to bowl this again.
Another bouncer but this one is too short. Brooks ducks under it easily.
Bumper down the leg side. No problems for Brooks to evade it.
Another shortish one on the pads, Brooks nudges it towards short fine leg.
A sharp bouncer this time, Brooks somehow manages to fend it off.
Length delivery on middle, Brooks pushes it wide of the man at mid on and call for a single.
Short and down the leg side. Left alone.
Floated on off, Brooks defends it.
On off, blocked by SB.
Tossed up on off, Brooks blocks it.
Floated on the stumps, Brooks keeps it out.
Shorter on off, Brooks gets on his back foot and defends it.
On the pads, Brooks flicks it to the on side and gets a single to keep the strike.
Short of a length just outside off, Brooks drops his hands and lets it go to the keeper.
Short again and on the pads, this time Brooks looks to flick but misses.
Short and outside off, punched towards point.
Short and around off, Brooks keeps it out.
Bouncer but too short. Brooks ducks under it.
Back of a length ball around off, blocked off the back foot.
Full and around off and middle, flicked towards mid-wicket.
Slower through the air around off, turning in. Brathwaite stays on the back foot and works it towards the leg side.
Around off and turning in, Brathwaite comes forward and blocks it.
Goes short and Brathwaite pounces on the chance as he pulls it through deep square leg. Sibley gives it a chase as they take three.
Full and around off, Brooks plays it to deep point for an easy run.
Very full on off, easy block for Brathwaite. These two are reading Bess brilliantly.
Bouncer but direction is outside off so Brooks easily sways away.
Shortish around the body. Brooks hops and drops it towards the leg side.
This one is down the leg side. Brooks has no business with it.
Another one down the leg side but Brooks tries flicking this time around but fails to connect.
Back of a length and around off, blocked nicely.
Goes full, Brooks flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Floated on the pads, flicked towards the leg side.
Around off, Brooks comes forward and blocks it nicely.
Very full and outside off, pushed towards mid off for an easy single.
Floated on off, blocked coming forward by Brathwaite.
Quicker one on the stumps, blocked off the back foot.
FOUR! Slammed through the covers as Bess once again bowls it full and outside off. Root gives it a chase but the ball wins the race to the fence.
Short and outside off, Brooks cuts but finds point.
Down the leg side. Left alone.

FOUR! Brooks enters into the 40s with a solid punch. Short and outside off, Brooks goes on the back foot and punches it between point and cover. Both the fielders gives it a chase but once again the ball wins the race.
Shortish but down the leg side so Brooks has no problem leaving it alone.
Landed around off and middle on a shortish length, blocked off the back foot.
Ouch! That's a good bumper from Stokes, aiming the ribs. Brooks tries to duck under it but gets hit on the elbow. Shows no emotions though and goes to his partner at the other end.
Good length ball around off, pushed towards covers.
Landed around off on a length, Brathwaite looks to defend but the ball takes the outer half of the bat and goes towards point.
On the pads, this one is worked towards mid-wicket.
Another fuller one, Brathwaite pushes it towards mid on.
Goes short this time but Brathwaite pulls it toward fine leg for an easy run. Kept it down nicely by rolling his wrists there.
Slightly shorter and around off, Brooks is solid in defense.
A bouncer around off and middle, Brathwaite takes it on and pulls it to deep square leg for a single. Once again, he rolled his wrists nicely to keep the pull shot down.
Shortish and around off, blocked off the back foot nicely.
This one is down the leg side and Brooks tries to pull but misses.
A bumper around middle and leg. Brooks ducks under it.
And another one and once again easily negotiated by Brooks. England might have to change their plan of bowling bouncer from Stokes' end.
Shorter and around off, Brooks defends it solidly off his back foot.
Good length ball on off, Brathwaite pushes it through covers gently and a single is taken.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
FOUR! Guided nicely! Good length ball just around off, Brooks comes forward and delicately guides it through the gully region. Stokes gives it a chase but he cannot cut it off.
Shortish and around off, blocked off the back foot.
Around off on a good length, Brooks is solid in defense.
Good length ball around off, shapes away after pitching as Brooks tries to defend.

OUT! Caught & Bowled! Stokes is the man, once again! He kept bowling the short stuff and has got the reward. This one is not as short as the other ones but Brathwaite is on the back foot as he tries to work it on the leg side. He though ends up getting a leading edge and the ball balloons towards Stokes. A simple chance for him and he accepts it. They check for the legality of the ball but Stokes is fine. A fine knock from Brathwaite comes to an end.
Outside off, left alone.
Good bumper but little too short as Chase ducks under it.
Another well directed bouncer. Chase hops and manages to block it.
Shortish again but this one is just outside off, Chase evades it well.

A couple to open the account for Chase as he taps this short ball outside off through point. End of a successful over by Stokes. This also brings up the 200 for West Indies who still trail by 268 runs.
Good length delivery around off, Brooks keeps it out.
Landed around off on a good length, Brooks keeps it out.
Beaten! In the probing line just outside off. Brooks looks to defend but gets beaten.
Good length ball around off, blocked off the front foot.
FOUR! Brooks moves to 49.  Slightly short and outside off, Brooks goes on the back foot and cuts it through gully for a boundary.

FOUR LEG BYES! A length ball down the leg side. Brooks looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Buttler moves to his left to stop but fails to do so and the ball races to the fine leg fence. 61 more needed to avoid the follow-on.
Stokes continues to bang it short. It is just around off. Chase drops his bat and sways away.
Short again, this time Chase rides the bounce and blocks it well.
This one is down the leg side. Chase lets it be.
Another short one and Chase ducks under it easily.
One more short ball, Chase hops and manages to fend it away.
Another one but way over the head of Chase.
FIFTY FOR BROOKS! Second in Tests. A very fine knock so far. He has played with a lot of control. He gets there by working this length ball on the pads behind square leg for a couple of runs.
Full and around off, pushed towards point.
A good length ball on off, defended towards mid on.
Short and just outside off, Brooks rides the bounce and taps it through point for a couple of runs.
Down the leg side. Brooks goes for the mighty flick but misses.
Good length ball on middle, a solid block to end the over.
Short and around the body, Chase tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
Good bumper but Brooks ducks under nicely.
Another short ball but down the leg side. Brooks thinks to hammer it via a pull but lets it alone in the end.
Another good bouncer but Brooks has been around for a while now so he has no problem evading it.
And one more short ball and once again Brooks ducks it away easily.
Flatter on off, pushed towards mid-wicket.
Shortish and around off, blocked.
Full and on the pads, Chase flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Full and on the pads again, Chase flicks it to the right of Sibley at deep square leg. Two taken before he can return the ball to the keeper.
Flatter and around off, pushed towards cover. Brooks wants a single but Chase says no.
Back of a length ball on the body, Chase tucks it towards deep square leg for 2 more.
Short again but down the leg side. Chase watches it go to the keeper.
Another short ball, this one is well directed by Broad. Chase is late in getting away. The ball hits his right shoulder and goes towards fine leg. A leg bye taken.

FOUR! Not a convincing stroke though and it wasn't too far away from diving Buttler. Perfect line and perfect length by Broad. Brooks had to play at it. He ends up gloving it behind. Buttler throws himself to his right but fails to get to the ball. It races to the fine leg fence.
Outside off, left alone.
Shortish and around off, blocked off the back foot.
Full and on middle, flicked towards square leg.
Another fuller one, this time Chase pushes it towards mid on and calls for a quick run.
Floated on off on a fuller area, Brooks blocks it out.
Flatter and around off, worked down the leg side.
Full and around off, Brooks eases a single through covers. Chase to face the final ball before Tea. Can he negotiate it?
Yes, he has negotiated as he works this shortish ball towards mid-wicket for a single. TEA ON DAY 4!
England continue with their short stuff as Broad bangs this short but down the leg side. Chase ducks under.
Shortish and around off, Chase keeps it out.
Another short one but again the line is wrong, down the leg side. Chase lets it be.
Shorter around the body. This time Chase is on the back foot to defend.
A bumper on middle, Chase evades it well.
Bumper again but too short. Chase ducks under it easily.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and around off, driven back to the bowler.
Quicker one jut outside off, Brooks waits for it and then guides it towards third man. A couple taken.
On the pads, blocked back to the bowler.

RUN OUT CHANCE MISSED! That was sloppy from Brooks. Full toss around off, Brooks forces it towards mid off and calls for a run. He though is very slow as Sibley gets to the ball quickly and fires the throw at the non-striker's end. Had he hit, Brooks would've had to head to the pavilion.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Short ball outside off, Brooks sways away from it.
Another one! The barrage of bouncers continue from Broad from one end. Brooks does well to sway away.
Short and on the body, blocks off the back foot.
Brilliant from Broad. Like Stokes, he too is continuing with the short stuff. Brooks hops and tries to fend it away. He is hit on the gloves and the ball goes towards gully.
Another one but this does not bounce much. Brooks sits low though and the ball goes over him.
Another short ball to end the over as Brooks ducks under well.
Shortish around off, worked towards the leg side.
Full and on off and middle, blocked towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Drilled down the ground. Bess bowls a very full ball outside off. Chase opens his arms and drills it through mid off for a boundary.
Floated around off and middle, blocked.
Another full ball, pushed towards mid off by Chase.
Fuller and around off, Chase comes forward and looks to defend but the ball takes thick outside edge and rolls towards short third man. A single taken.
Shortish and around off, blocked off the back foot by Chase.
Another back of a length ball outside off, this one is tapped towards point.
Good length ball around off and middle, Chase looks to defend but the ball takes thick inside edge and goes towards deep square leg. A single taken.
Ripper! That came back in nicely after pitching on good length as Brooks tried to drive. It went just over the timbers. Excellent change of length from Broad.

EDGY FOUR! Another fine delivery by Broad. Shortish and around off, Brooks tries to drop his hand and avoid it but ends up getting a thick outside edge. The ball goes past the diving second slip fielder and into the third man fence.
Down the leg side. Brooks looks to work it on the leg side but misses. Buttler fails to gather it cleanly down the leg side and allows a bye.
Length delivery around off, played back to the bowler.
Shortish and around off, Brooks blocks it off his back foot.
Landed around off on a good length, Brooks does well to block off his back foot.
Back of a length ball on middle, Brooks defends it back to the bowler.
Goes full this time, pushed back to the bowler.
Good effort from Broad at mid off. Saves runs for the side. Fuller and around off, Brooks strokes it to the right side of Broad who is at mid off. He makes a diving stop to his right. A single taken.
Confusion but safe. A length ball around off, Brooks pushes it towards covers and calls for a single.

OUT! LBW! Pinned in front! The second new ball has done the trick for England. A length ball around off, coming in nicely. Brooks is late in getting his bat down to work it on the leg side and gets pinned in front of the stumps. Broad and co. appeal and the umpire raises the finger quickly. Second batsman to fall in the 50s for West Indies. A solid innings nonetheless from him. They are still 28 behind from avoiding the follow-on.
Back of a length ball around off, Blackwood keeps it out.
Another shortish one around off, Blackwood defends it off his back foot.
Play and a miss! Short and wide outside off, Blackwood goes after it but misses.
Full and on off, driven firmly but straight to mid off.
Short and around off, Chase waits on the back foot to defend.
Outside off, left alone.

NOT OUT! Pitching outside leg and Chase survives. Top review from him. A very full ball on the pads, Chase tries to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. A loud appeal from Curran and the other English follows and the umpire raises his finger. Chase quickly reviews it. Let's see what replays show. First, the front foot. It is fine and there is no bat involved either. Where is it pitching? Just outside leg and the on-field decision will be changed. Excellent review from him.
EDGY FOUR! Good length ball just around off, Chase looks to defend but gets a thick inside edge. The ball goes over the stumps and into the fine leg fence.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Good length ball around middle and leg, Chase tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Landed around off on a good length, Chase keeps it out.
Fuller and on off, Chase pushes it towards covers and takes a quick single.
Shortish and around off, Blackwood stays on the back foot to defend.

OUT! Bowled! The hero with the willoow in Southampton walks back for a duck in Manchester. Broad gets his man and he has second one of the game. Big wicket for the hosts here not just because Blackwood is a dangerous man but also because England now have their tail up. After bowling shorter, Broad goes a bit fuller on off, the ball stays a bit low off the deck. Blackwood looks to defend but the low bounce does him and he hears the awful sound of the timber. Music to Broad's ears though.
Ohh, close! Length ball outside off, Dowrich looks to defend but misses.
On the body, Dowrich turns it to the leg side. End of a very good over from Start Broad.
Outside off, left alone.
Another leave as this one is outside off on a good length.
Shortish and around off, Chase stays on the back foot to defend.
FOUR! Drilled through the covers! Full and outside off, Chase leans into the shot and smashes it through the covers.
Outside off, Chase shoulders arms.
Good length ball around off, blocked towards point off the back foot.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Fuller and just around off, Dowrich pushes it towards mid off.

OUT! LBW! Pitching in line and hitting the stumps. So, the review does not save Dowrich. He goes for a duck as well. Broad is making the new ball talk and causing trouble here for West Indies. A length ball angled in from just outside off, Dowrich tries to flick it off his back foot but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal follows and the umpire agrees. Dowrich takes it upstairs. Let's see if he can survive. The front foot is fine. Any bat? No, confirms the Ultra Edge. Pitching in line and hitting the wickets. So, Dowrich has to go and he takes one review along with him. West Indies still need 18 to avoid the follow-on.
Good length ball around off, Holder blocks it off his front foot.
Another length ball around off, Holder defends it nicely.
Very full ball on middle, Holder strokes it towards mid on.
Outside off, Chase shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball outside off, Chase leaves it alone.
On the pads, Chase flicks it to the on side for a run.
Ohh! Excitement from the English fielders. Good length ball outside off, it comes back in a bit. Holder looks to defend but gets beaten and the ball just about misses the outside edge of his willow.
Length ball around off, this time Holder blocks it.
Around off, Holder gets on his back foot and punches it through covers for a couple to get off the mark.
Length ball outside off, Chase looks to defend but the ball shapes away.

Risky run but safe in the end. Broad bowls it full on off, Chase pushes it towards mid off and calls off for a quick run. Holder responds, Woakes gets to the ball quickly and has a shy at the bowler's end but his throw is a poor one.
On off, Holder blocks it.
Outside off, Holder leaves it.
Length delivery on off, Holder defends it to point.
Length ball on off, Holder blocks it to get through the over.
Away from the off pole, Chase leaves it alone.
Length ball on off, Chase defends it.
Fuller on off, Chase pushes it to cover.
On off, Roston gets behind it and blocks it.
FOUR! Easy pickings and West Indies now just 10 away from avoiding follow-on. Stokes strays on the pads, Chase lofts his flick over mid-wicket and gets a boundary.
Around off, Chase pushes it to point.
Good length ball on off, Holder defends it.

OUT! Caught! Woakes comes into the attack and gets a wicket. We are in for a cracker here as West Indies have two wickets in hand and need  to avoid follow on. First wicket of the game for Woakes and it is the big one of the West Indies skipper. Excellent bowling from Woakes. He bowls it around off, in the channel of uncertainty and makes it shape a tad. Just enough to trouble Holder. He looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge to first slip. The English skipper, judges it well and takes a good catch.
Length ball outside off, Roach leaves it.
Another one outside off, Kemar lets it carry to the keeper.
Good length ball on off, Roach defends it with a dead bat.
Down the leg side, Roach looks to flick but misses. End of a very good over from Woakes.
On the pads, Chase looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball on middle and leg, it swings in a bit but Chase does enough to defend it.
On the pads, Chase flicks it towards square leg and looks for two but the fielder is quick to get there and they have to be happy with one.

NOT OUT! There is a spike as the ball goes past the bat and England lose their review. Good length delivery around leg and middle, Roach looks to flick but misses. The England players appeal but the umpire turns it down. Root thinks about it and refers it. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge shows a spike as the ball goes past the bat. Just a feather but enough for England to lose a review and Roach to survive.
Length ball on off, Roach blocks it.
Fuller on off, Kemar manages to keep it out and survive.
Length ball outside off, Chase punches it towards cover and gets a single.
Length ball well away from the off stump, Roach is happy to leave it.
Good length ball on off, Roach defends it.
Length delivery outside off, Roach looks to defend but then pulls his bat back in.
Fuller on off, Roach lunges forward and defends it.
Good leave! Outside off, Roach bends forward and then lets the ball carry to the keeper.
FOUR! Just one more hit  needed now to avoid the follow on. Curran bowls it on middle and leg, looking for a LBW but Chase is quick to flick it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On the pads, Chase glances it towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! West Indies have avoided the follow on. Short ball on the body, Chase pulls it through square leg for a boundary.
On the leg side, Chase flicks it to the on side.
Shorter and around off, Chase pushes it through covers for two.
In the air but just short. Fuller on middle, Chase looks to loft it over mid on but does not get the elevation. The ball falls on Woakes at mid on. He dives but still can't reach.
Good length ball on middle, Roach works it towards the leg side and calls for a run but Chase says no.
Full and outside off, Roach lets it be.
Landed around off and middle, Roach works it towards mid-wicket.
Very full ball on the pads, Roach tries to guide it down to fine leg but misses to connect.
Shortish and on middle, Roach hops and defends it out.

Edged but falls short. A fuller ball just around off, Roach looks to defend but it takes thick outside edge and goes to the right of Stokes. He dives that side but the ball falls well short of him. Saves a boundary though.
Good length ball on middle, Chase works it towards the leg side.
FOUR! Chase is dealing in boundaries now! Full and outside off, he creams it through the covers.
Slightly short and on middle, Chase keeps it out.

Three more for Chase and he gets closer to his half ton. This is not delicate though as it takes thick outside edge and races towards third man. The slip fielder gives it a chase and keeps it to three.

FOUR! More runs, this time for Roach and again not from the middle of the bat but Roach and West Indies won't mind it. Full and around off, Roach looks to drive but gets thick outside edge and the ball goes to the third man fence through gully.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Shortish and just outside off, Chase tries to tap it through covers off his back foot but misses.
A ripper from Woakes! Shortish and just outside off, Chase plays at it but misses.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, Chase blocks it towards cover.
Another leave as Woakes bowls this length ball outside off.
Good length delivery around off, Chase pushes it towards point.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Down the leg side on a good length, Roach tries to tickle it to fine leg but fails to get any bat. Buttler does well to dive to his left to grab the ball.
Full and around off and middle, Roach tucks it towards square leg for a single.
A couple for Chase and he gets to his half ton. A full ball on the pads, he flicks it towards deep square leg.
Good length ball around off, Chase looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half of the bat and goes towards square leg. A run taken.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

OUT! LBW! Excellent review from England and they are just one wicket away from batting again. Roston Chase's brilliant innings comes to an end. Another very good ball from Woakes and he has his second of the innings. Full and quick around off, Chase looks to defend but misses due to the pace and the movement. He gets hit on the pads but there is some noise. England players appeal but the umpire turns it down. Root has a word with Woakes and decides to take it upstairs. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge shows that the bat hit the pad and not the ball. Time for the Ball Tracker and it shows three reds. Chase has to walk back and England now have two tailenders at the crease.
Full around off, Gabriel blocks it.
Outside off, Shannon looks to defend but misses.

Ouch that must have hurt. We all know it did. Good length ball around leg, Gabriel looks to defend but misses and gets hit flush on the box. Ouch! Roach is having a laugh but bet Gabriel is not enjoying a bit.
Bouncer! Gabriel sits under it.

OUT! Bowled! The slower ball does the trick and West Indies are bowled out now. Woakes smartly takes the pace off this one and bowls it on a length, Gabriel looks to defend but gets deceived by the lack of pace. The ball also moves away a bit, squaring up Gabriel and hitting the off pole. West Indies bowled out for 287! Trail by 182.
Runs straight away! A good length ball around off, Stokes looks to drive but the ball takes the outer half of the bat and goes towards covers. A single taken.
Very full ball around off, Buttler does well to block it out.
Another fuller one, this one is played back to the bowler. Roach tries to field but misses as the ball hits the stumps at the bowler's end.

OUT! DRAGGED ON! Buttler goes for a duck and the plan to open with him fails. Full and outside off, Buttler sees the chance of freeing his arms. He throws his bat but ends up dragging the ball on his stumps. Idea start for West Indies as Buttler could've score really quickly.
A single on the first ball. Full and around off, pushed towards cover for a single.
Outside off, left alone. Successful over for West Indies ends.
Back of a length ball on middle, Crawley looks to pull but fails to time it well. It drops towards the leg side off the upper part of his bat. Stokes calls for a single.
Length ball around off and middle, Stokes punches it down to long on for a single.
Bouncer on middle and leg, Crawley sits under it.
Brilliant ball from Gabriel. Bangs it short and makes it to come back in. Crawley tries to defend but the ball sneaks through and goes over the stumps.
Another ripper! Just past the outside edge. Gabriel bowls this in the channel, just outside off. Crawley has to play at it. He does so but the slight away movement means he is beaten.
Short and around off and middle, this time he pulls it down to deep square leg for a single. A very good first over from Gabriel too.
Flicked off the pads for a couple of runs. Full and around middle and leg, Crawley flicks it through mid-wicket and before the mid on can get around, two taken.
No run. Shortish and just outside off, Crawley punches it towards short cover.
Almost another drag on! A good length ball just around off, Crawley looks to drive but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
Length delivery around off, Crawley pushes it towards point and takes a quick run.
Low full toss around off, Stokes skips down the track to launch it over long on but mistimes it just wide of the mid on fielder. Gets just a single.
Fuller and around off, played back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball on  off, Stokes pulls it but there is protection at deep square leg so just a single.

FOUR! It does not matter how and where they come as long as they keep on coming. Length delivery outside off, Crawley looks to play it on the off side but gets a thick outside edge which takes the ball wide and past of the man at gully for a boundary.
Short ball on middle, Crawley pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
In the air but safe. Full on middle and off, Stokes looks to go over long off but does not get the distance. It goes high in the air but falls short of long off who comes running in.
On the pads, Crawley looks to flick but the ball goes off his thigh pad for a single.
Length ball outside off, Stokes looks to hit but misses.

OUT! BOWLED! The middle stump goes cartwheeling. Roach gets his second wicket of the innings and England's aggressive approach is backfiring here. Good length ball on middle and off, Crawley looks to go down town but misses and the ball takes the middle stump with it. Great sight for any bowler but a fast bowler's delight.
On the pads, Root flicks it to the on side and gets off the mark with a single. The lead now stands at 200!
On the pads, Stokes glances it to the leg side and gets a run.
Fuller on off, Joe pushes it to mid off.
Good ball. Length delivery pitching outside off and coming back in, Root looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Length ball outside off, Root strokes it behind square on the off side and gets run. He will keep the strike.
No Ball! Shorter but down the leg side, Root looks to pull but misses. It is called a No Ball though as Gabriel oversteps his line.
Short ball on off this time, Root pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for one.
Length ball on middle and leg, Stokes  taps it towards third man and gets a couple.
Outside off, Stokes looks to cut but misses.
Full around off, Stokes plays it towards long on and looks for two but gets only one.
Good length ball on off, Root pulls it towards fine leg and gets to the other end.
Outside off, Stokes throws his bat at it but it goes towards third man off the bottom edge. Root and Stokes look for two but have to do with one.
Good length ball outside off, Stokes comes down the track and slams it to deep cover for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
Shortish around off, Root taps it towards point and calls for a run.
Good length ball just around off, Stokes pushes it through covers and calls for two straightaway. Root though denies the second.
A couple for Root but off the inside edge as he tries to punch this length ball just around off towards the off side. It goes to fine leg and they take two.
Full and just outside off, Root goes for the drive but misses. The ball kept low and went to the keeper on the bounce.
Short and wide outside off, Stokes cuts it to deep point for two more. Didn't time it well there.
Excellent shot but just one! Fuller and around off, Stokes drives it through mid off powerfully but Joseph at long off cuts it off.
Beauty from Shannon! Slightly short and outside off, Root comes forward and looks to drive but misses.
Landed around off on a good length, Root guides it down to third man for a single.
Swing and a miss! A fuller ball just outside off, Stokes looks to launch it over long off but doesn't connect.

A single to end Day 4. A length delivery on middle and leg, Stokes tucks it towards mid on and calls for two but the fielder charges in and Stokes has to settle for a single. With that, it is STUMPS ON DAY 4.
Run straightaway! And Stokes clears his intentions on the first ball. A fuller ball outside off, he powers it to deep cover for a single.
Good length ball just around off, Root plays it towards point.
A single for Root now as he works this length ball on the pads towards fine leg.
FOUR! Stokes gets the chance of freeing his arms and he does so nicely! Slightly short and just outside off, Stokes is down the track to punch it through the cover region for a boundary.
SIX! Monstrous! England need a few more of these and Stokes can certainly do that. Full and just outside off, Stokes comes down the track and slams it over long off for a huge six.
14 from the over! Superb start for England. Wide outside off, Stokes once again gives it charge and punches it wide of the long off fielder. Two taken before the fielder can get around.
Overthrow! A length delivery around off, Root  pushes it towards point and takes a single. The fielder there fires a throw at the keeper's end but misses and concedes an extra run.
Down the leg side, Root tries to flick but misses.
Short and wide outside off, Root looks to cut but fails to connect.
Good length ball outside off, Root guides it down to third man for a single.

Dropped! Oh dear! A simple chance has been put down. Gabriel is fuming! John Campbell is the man. A length ball just outside off, Stokes looks to clear the long off fence again but he ends up miscuing it this time. It goes towards deep cover where Campbell settles himself nicely, gets both the hands but fails to hold on. Single for Stokes.
Full and just outside off, Root drives it towards deep cover for a single.
On the pads, Root plays it towards mid on and calls for a single.
FOUR! Hammered down the ground! This is some batting from Stokes. A full ball around off, Stokes gives it a charge and sends it over mid off for another boundary.
Good bumper! Sharp from Roach as he realizes that fuller ball has been dispatched. Roach bends his back and bowls a sharp bouncer. Stokes does well to evade.
WIDE! Another short ball, this one is outside off. Stokes lets it go. Wided by the umpire.
Good length ball around off, Stokes mistimes it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Landed around off, Root tucks it towards mid on and takes a run.
Another short ball, this time Stokes charges down and pulls it down to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Low full toss around off and middle, Stokes powers it to deep mid-wicket. Roach does well to stop the ball with his boot. Two taken and it brings 50-run stand between the two.
Back of a length ball around off, pulled for a single. England's lead now reads 250.
Short ball around off and middle, Root pulls it towards mid-wicket.
Another short of a length ball around middle, Root works it towards deep square leg for a run.
Swing and a miss! Good length ball outside off, Stokes makes room outside off and tries to hammer it down town but fails to connect.
Two more as this length ball outside off is smashed to the right side of the long off fielder.

Direct hit and it would've been interesting. A length ball around off, Root pushes it towards gully and calls for a run. The fielder there fires the throw at the striker's end but misses. Stokes is happy to have the strike.
Full and outside off, Stokes drills it towards long off and scampers for two more. Excellent running between the wickets.
Bumper and a good one too. Stokes does well to evade it.
Very full ball around off, Stokes drills it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Down the leg side. Root looks to pull but fails to connect. Dowrich does well to gather it on his left.
Length ball just around off, Root stays on the back foot and guides it down to third man. They think for the second but the fielder there is quick to the ball so they settle for the single only.
Full and around off and middle, Root looks to flick but ends up getting it off the inside edge towards third man. A single taken.
Good length ball outside off, Stokes looks to hammer it again but fails to connect.

SIX & FIFTY FOR STOKES! He has nailed this time around. 22nd Test half-century for him. He is making sure that the runs come quickly for his team. A fuller ball just outside off, Stokes hammers it over long off for a biggie.
Short and around off, this one is pulled down to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Good length ball around off, Root looks to pull but ends up getting a bottom edge down to fine leg for a run.
A single and Stokes will keep the strike for the next over as he plays this full toss down to deep square leg.

Low full toss on middle and leg, Stokes whips it to the left of deep mid-wicket and looks for two. The fielder though gets to the ball quickly and Root comes out of his crease. The skipper is sent back but luckily the though at the keeper's end is a poor one and Joe can get back in safely with his dive.
On the pads, Root flicks it to fine leg and gets a single.

NOT OUT! Waste of a review. The ball is pitching outside leg so we don't even need to go to check the height. Length delivery on leg, Stokes looks to pull but misses and gets hit on the box. West Indies player put in a mild appeal which is turned down. Holder decides to take the review. Replay rolls in and shows that the ball is pitching outside leg.
On the pads, Stokes looks to flick but misses and Dowrich fails to gather it cleanly allowing them to steal a bye.
Outside off, Root leaves it alone.
Short ball on middle and off, Root pulls it and keeps the strike.

OUT! RUN OUT! Root sacrifices his wicket for Stokes and the team. Joseph starts with a ball down the leg side. Root looks to flick but misses. Stokes is on his bike to get on strike. Root keeps his head down and runs. Dowrich throws the ball to Holder who comes from mid off and whips the bails off. Root is nowhere in the frame and he has to depart.

Not Out! Another review has been lost by the West Indies. Pitching around leg, Stokes looks to whip it over on the leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads. Holder decides to take the review. Replay rolls in and it shows that the ball is pitching outside leg again...
Down the leg side, Stokes looks to flick but misses.
Wide outside off, Stokes throws his bat but misses.
On middle, Stokes plays it wide of long on and gets a couple.
Full and wide outside off, Stokes strokes it wide of third man and gets another brace.

NOT OUT! West Indies have lost all their reviews and that has happened very quickly. Full toss on the pads, Pope looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. Holder apeals and in the meantime the batter take a run as the ball goes to the leg side. Jason decides to signal the 'T'. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge shows a little bit of spike as the ball goes past the bat.
Outside off, Stokes swings but misses.
Fuller outside off, Stokes plays it through covers and gets a single.
On the pads, Pope tucks it behind square on the leg side and gets a single.
SIX! Stokes has come in T20 mode and that is what his team needs. When he is in such a mood you cannot bowl him in his arc. Holder bowls it full around off, Stokes slams it over long off for a six.
FOUR! Delicate from Stokes. Short ball around off, Stokes waits for it and then guides it fine towards third man. Roach there gives it a chase but comes second best.
Fuller on off and middle, Pope plays the reverse paddle and gives the strike to Stokes.
On the pads, Stokes flicks it to the on side and gets a single.
Good fielding! On the pads, Pope plays it fine down the leg side. Hope runs to his right from fine leg and does very well to stop the ball before the ropes. Saves 2 for his side.
Back of a length delivery around off, Pope runs it down to third man and gets a single. Lead is now of 294 runs.
Full and wide outside off, Stokes stretches and plays it to deep point for a single.
FOUR! Very good shot and the lead now stretches to 299! Length ball outside off, Pope hangs back and cuts it through point for a boundary. England get the boundary they were looking for in the over.
Full toss down the leg side, Stokes looks to flick but misses.
Smart from Holder. He has once again bowled one down the leg side, Stokes looks to flick but misses. The umpire has had a word with Holder for the negative line.
This time on the pads, Stokes flicks it behind square leg and gets a couple as the fielder there dives to his left and saves a couple. Lead past 300 now, it's 301.
EDGED AND FOUR! Length ball outside off, Stokes looks to slash it on the off side but gets a thick outside edge which goes wide of the keeper and to the fence.

Full and wide outside off, Stokes plays it wide of third man and gets a couple. One ball remaining in this over, it could also be the last ball of England's innings as they look ready to take the field.
WIDE! Holder bowls one down the leg side and the umpire has signalled it as wide. Stokes also steals a run. So one more ball.

On the pads, Pope glances it to the on side and gets a single to finish the over. Root comes to the balcony and he has called his players off. England declare at 129/3. West Indies need 312 to win the Test!
Runs for West Indies straightaway! Three of them. A fuller ball on the pads, Brathwaite flicks it down to deep square leg for three.
Good length ball around off, pushed toward point.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Campbell is off the mark in a fine fashion. Full and outside off, Campbell leans into the shot and drives it through point for a boundary.

OUT! Caught Behind! A last second review but it is a successful one. A full ball outside off, Campbell once again looks to drive it through the covers but fails to connect. There is a loud appeal but nothing from Buttler from behind the wickets. Root thinks and thinks and calls for the review at the last moment. And, the replays show that there is a clear spike. So, England have drawn first blood in the very first over.
Outside off, Hope lets it be. Successful first over for England.

FOUR! Fine shot from Brathwaite. Good length ball outside the off stump, Brathwaite punches it through the covers. The fielder chases it, makes a diving stop. The umpires check if it is a clean stop. It is not is what the replays confirm so a boundary for Brathwaite.
Around off, solidly defended.
Shortish and around off and middle, Brathwaite keeps it out.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
On middle and leg, this one is played towards mid-wicket.
Very full ball on middle, Brathwaite blocks it out nicely.
Good length ball on off, Hope defends it with a dead bat.
Length ball way outside off, Hope leaves it alone.
On the pads, Hope flicks it stylishly towards fine leg and gets a single.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Broad overcooks this delivery and bowls it too full around off, Brathwaite gets on his front foot and drives it wonderfully through mid off for a boundary.
On the pads, Brathwaite flicks it to the on side.
Bouncer! Brathwaite watches it closely and sits under it.
Length ball on off, Hope defends it off the front foot.
Back of a length ball on off, Shai defends it.
On the pads, Hope looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Beauty! Good length ball pitching outside off and coming back in. Hope looks to play it straight but misses. Shai is lucky as the ball was just whiskers away from the edge.
Length ball on off, Hope pushes it to point.
Inswinging full ball on off, Hope keeps his eyes on the ball and blocks it right under his eyes.
On the pads, Brathwaite looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pad.
On off, Brathwaite blocks.
Outside off, KB leaves it alone.
Good length ball on the fourth stump line, Brathwaite is aware of his off pole and leaves it alone.

Oh! This one keeps low but unfortunately it misses the stump by just a bit. Good length ball outside off, it shapes in a bit but does not come back enough to take the edge of Brathwaite's defensive willow or stump.
Broad over corrects and misses his line as he delivers this way down the leg side.
Good length ball on middle and off, Hope defends it with a dead bat.
On the pads, Hope flicks it towards fine leg and gets to the other end.
Down the leg side, Brathwaite looks to flick but misses.
Length ball on off, KB pushes it to mid off.
Good seam movement as he bowls it on a length and makes it to shape away. Brathwaite defends it towards point.
Length ball on off, Brathwaite once again blocks it to get through the over.
Good length ball just outside off, Hope looks to defend but misses.
Full ball around off and middle, Hope keeps it out.

Appeal from behind the wickets but Broad suggests it is high. A length ball around off, comes back in sharply. Hope looks to block but misses to get hit on the pad. The keeper and the slip cordon appeal but Broad does not and tells it's too high. The replays later roll in and confirm the same.
Another one that comes back in from around off, this time Hope does well to block it away.
In the channel outside off, this time Hope covers his stumps and lets it be.
Landed around off on a good length, blocked by Hope off his back foot.
Length ball down the leg side. Brathwaite lets it be.
Shortish and on the body, Brathwaite hops and works it down to fine leg for a single.
A solid front foot block by Hope this time to this good length ball around off.
Full and just around off, Hope looks to cream it through covers but fails to time it well. It went uppishly towards the cover fielder.
On the pads, Hope nudges it to fine leg for a single.

OUT! LBW! That is plumb and Brathwaite is not taking the DRS. He just walks as he knows where he was standing. A good length ball that comes back in from just around off, Brathwaite looks to defend but misses to get hit on the back pad. Huge appeal follows and the umpire agrees. Brathwaite has a word with Hope but keeps walking. The replays later show that it would've been umpire's call on hitting the wickets.
A length ball just around off, Hope keeps it out off his front foot.
Outside off, a leave from Hope.
FOUR! Slammed through the covers. Full and outside off, he frees his arms and creams it through the cover region and the ball races away to the fence.
Good length ball around off blocked.

OUT! Knocked him over with a beauty! Another one bites the dust and England are on fire. Brilliant from Broad. A brilliant ball again. Pitches just outside off and nips back in sharply to beat the inside edge and topple the timbers behind. West Indies in all sorts of trouble early on.
A bouncer around off, Chase ducks under it.
Shortish ball outside off, Brooks lets it go to the keeper.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On the pads, Brooks flicks it towards fine leg for a single to get off the mark.
Superb delivery from Woakes. A slightly shortish ball just around off, Chase pokes at it but gets beaten.
Very full around off, pushed towards point.
Landed on a good length on middle, Chase works it on the leg side.
Good length ball on middle, Brooks works it towards deep square leg for a run.
Outside off on a good length, Chase leaves it alone.
Another leave as this one too is well outside off.

Huge appeal but that was clearly going down. It was angled in from outside off, Chase tried to work it on the leg side but missed to get hit on the pads. An appeal from England but nothing from the umpire.
Good leave, very good leave. A length delivery just around off, Chase covers his stumps and lets it go.

NOT OUT! Missing the leg stump by some distance. A waste of a review from them. Good length ball on middle, comes back in once again. Chase tries to flick but misses and is hit on the pads. A loud appeal from Broad and others but not out says the umpire. Root has a word with his bowler and opts for the review. Time for the replays. Front foot is fine. Is it hitting the stumps? Ball Tracker says no, missing the leg pole. So, Chase stays to return for the second session as it is LUNCH ON DAY 5!
A good length ball outside off to begin the session. Brooks shoulders arms.
Good length ball around off, blocked by Brooks.
Another good length ball around off, Brooks pushes it towards point.
Slightly shorter in length, Brooks keeps it out off his back foot.
FOUR! Full and outside off, Brooks drives it nicely through point and the ball races away to the fence.
Good length ball around off, it is worked towards point for a run.
Fuller but outside off, Brooks lets it go to the keeper.

Poor shot from Brooks but Broad lured him doing this.He this time invites the batsman for the drive by bowling it full. Brooks obliges but the ball moves away to beat the outside edge. He could've easily left that alone.
Fuller again, this time Brooks pushes it back to Broad.
Another fuller one, pushed back to the bowler who gets down to field but makes a half stop as the ball goes towards mid on. No runs taken.
Outside off, left alone.
A back of a length ball but the line is not right for this one as it is down the leg side. Brooks has no problems leaving it alone.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Another leave as Woakes once again is slightly wide outside off on a good length.
Nice bowling. Slightly shortish and just outside off. Shapes away after pitching nicely as Chase tries to play but withdraws his bat away at the last moment.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards covers.
Full and on the pads, this time he flicks it towards deep square leg for a single to open his account.
Brooks lets this length ball outside off go to the keeper by covering his stumps.
In the channel outside off, shaping further away. An easy leave for Chase.
This time Woakes bowl it closer to the off stump and Chase pokes at it to get beaten. Lucky not to edge on that one.
On the pads this time, Chase tucks it towards fine leg for a run.
Shortish and around off, Brooks stays on the back foot and taps it towards the off side and takes a quick single.
FOUR! First boundary for Chase. A fuller length ball on middle and leg, Chase whips it to deep mid-wicket and the ball races to the fence.

OUT! LBW! No shot offered and Chase has to go. He will not review this. Broad has his third and West Indies in a massive, massive trouble. A length ball outside off, Chase thinks it will not come back in much and shoulders arms. However, to his surprise, the ball comes back in nicely and hits him on the pads. A loud appeal follows and the umpire raises his finger. Chase keeps walking and the replays show why. It would've been waste of a review had he taken that.
Good length ball around off and middle, Brooks blocks it out.
FOUR! Creamed through covers! Full and outside off, Brooks leans into the shot and smashes it through the covers. Two fielders give it a chase but the ball wins the race.
Full again and around off, Brooks once again times it well but finds mid off.
A leave as this one is outside off.
One more leave as Curran once again bowls this length ball outside off.
Third leave in a row as  Curran continues bowling way outside off.
Good length ball on off, Blackwood defends it with a straight bat.
Blackwood opens his account. Broad bowls it on middle and leg, Blackwood turns it to the leg side and takes a run to get off the mark.
Length ball on off, Brooks keeps it out.
Very full on off, Brooks blocks it towards mid off.
Effort ball from Broad. Brooks hops and dabs it onto the ground.
Full on off, Brooks plays it to mid on.

FOUR! Lucky though! Short and outside off, bouncer a little too extra. Surprising because even Broad and Woakes have not got that much bounce. Blackwood tries to leave it alone but the ball gets him big and takes the top edge and races to the fence over the leaping slip fielder.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Just over mid off. Blackwood is not worried about the fielder and he will continue to play his shots. Full and outside off, he lofts it over mid off for a boundary.
In the channel outside off, Blackwood lets it be..
FOUR! Third boundary in the over. Full and outside off again as Curran searches for some movement. Blackwood creams it through the covers and the ball races to the fence.
Full and on off, driven firmly but straight to mid off.
On off, defended by Brooks.

Appeal for LBW but turned down. Fuller around off, Brooks looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Broad continues his follow through and even celebrates as he thinks he has his man. The umpire though is unmoved and the batters take one as the ball goes towards backward point.
Down the leg side, Blackwood looks to flick but misses.
On the pads, Blackwood looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal again from Broad but once again not out says the umpire.
Good length ball on off, JB defends it off the front foot.
On the stumps, Blackwood blocks it.
Length ball on off, Brooks defends it.
On off, kept out.
Back of a length ball on off, Brooks punches it towards cover.
Outside off, Brooks leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Brooks is looking confident as he keeps this one out.
Calm and composed batting this from Brooks. Outside off, Brooks shoulders arms to it and gets through the over.
Starts his new spell with a good length ball on off, Blackwood pushes it off his back foot towards mid off.
On off, Blackwood blocks it.
On the pads, JB flicks it to the leg side and takes one.
On off, SB defends it.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Back of a length on off, Brooks defends it to get through the over.
Shortish and around off, punched towards covers.
Outside off, left alone.
Landed around off and middle, Blackwood keeps it out.
FOUR! Smashed over the cover region! Fuller and outside off, Blackwood hammers it over covers for a boundary. He is not going to miss out on any chance of opening his arms.
Around off on a good length, blocked back to the bowler.
A couple to end the over. A length ball on the pads, Blackwood tucks it towards deep mid-wicket and takes two.
Good length ball on middle, Brooks works it towards mid-wicket.
Another good length ball around off and middle, pushed towards mid on.

Leading edge! Full ball on middle, Brooks looks to flick but gets a leading edge. The ball takes the leading edge and goes through gully uppishly. Bess gives it a chase and saves a single as the batters return for the third on the throw.
Shortish and outside off, Blackwood looks to punch it but mistimes it as it hits the lower part of the bat.
Good length delivery on off, Blackwood keeps it out.
Shortish and on off, Blackwood does well to defend it out.
He starts with a full ball outside off, Brooks drives it to deep cover for a single.
Fuller and around off, driven to mid off by Blackwood.
Flatter and just outside off, Blackwood stays on the back foot and guides it to third man. Two taken.
Floated around off, firmly driven back to the bowler.
FOUR! Timed brilliantly! Everything about this ball was perfect. Full and outside off, Blackwood takes a step forward, leans into it and creams it to the left side of the man at mid off.
Shortish and around off, Blackwood pushes it towards mid-wicket off his back foot.
Around off on a good length, Brooks defends it out.
Very full around off, driven to mid off.

Appeal for caught behind but not out says the umpire. Nobody from the slip cordon is sure and neither the bowler and hence no review from them. Oh wait, it looks like there was some glove. Lucky, Brooks is a lucky man. A brilliant, effort ball from Woakes. It is short and just around off, Brooks hops and tries to let it go by dropping his hands. However, it takes the gloves and goes behind but none of the English players were sure so they do not opt for the review.
Down the leg side, Brooks looks to flick but misses.
Shortish and around off, Brooks is on the back foot to block it out.
Shortish and on the middle, Brooks works it towards deep square leg for two more.
Floated on off, Blackwood defends it.
FOUR! Floated on off, Blackwood strokes it wonderfully through mid off for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, this time there is protection at mid off so just one.
On the stumps, Brooks blocks it.
Gives this air on off, Brooks bends his back and keeps it out.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Good length ball on off, Blackwood defends it off his back foot.
Length ball outside off, Blackwood looks to defend but misses.
Fuller on off and middle, Blackwood plays it to mid on.

FOUR! Blackwood is doing what he did in the second innings of the first Test and England will be a tad worried now. Outside off, Blackwood loves the width and cuts it square behind square on the off side for a boundary.
On the pads, Blackwood looks to flick but misses and takes a leg bye as the ball goes off his thigh pad.
On middle and off, Shamarh strokes it through mid on and gets a couple.
Shortish ball around off and middle, worked behind square leg for two. 50-run stand is up between the two.
Shorter on off, blocked back to the bowler.
On off, played back to the bowler.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Floated on off, blocked towards the leg side.
Another full ball on off and middle, Blackwood blocks it off his front foot.
Outside off on a good length to begin the spell by Stokes. Brooks lets it be.
Good length ball around off, blocked.
Full and outside off, Brooks tries to drill it through covers but fails to connect.
Shortish and around off, blocked off the back foot.
Two more! Shortish and around off, Brooks stays on the back foot and tucks it to deep mid-wicket. Before the fielder can get to the ball, two taken.
Beaten! Lose shot from Brooks. He is going after anything which is outside off and it can be costly for him. This time he fails to connect as the ball goes past the outside edge.
Floated on off, Blackwood pushes it towards long on for a quick run.
Full and around off, driven to the cover fielder.
Fuller and around off, turned towards mid-wicket by Brooks.
Slightly short and just around off, Brooks stays on the back foot and tries to punch but gets a bottom edge. The ball bounces just near the crease and goes onto hit the grill of Buttler.
The batsman has punched that ball through the offside.
Beaten! A nice ball to end the over. It is a loopy ball just outside off Brooks tries to defend but is beaten.
Outside off, left alone.
Shortish and around off, Blackwood keeps it out.
Full and outside off, Blackwood goes after it but fails to connect.
Back of a length ball around off, Blackwood pushes it towards the off side.
Shortish and around off, this one is pushed towards point for a single.
Two to end the over! Shortish and on middle, Brooks tucks it towards deep square leg and gets two.
Floated fuller around off, blocked towards mid on.
Quicker one on the pads, this is worked towards square leg.
Full and on the pads again, once again flicked straight to square leg.
Shortish and around off and middle, Blackwood goes on the back foot to force it towards mid-wicket.
Another shortish one, turning in. Blackwood stays on the back foot to work it towards the right side of the square leg fielder. Two taken.
