And another short one, this time Blackwood pulls it to deep mid-wicket and takes one.
Back of a length ball around off, Blackwood hops and defends it out.
Shortish outside off, Blackwood punches it through covers for three. 100 up for West Indies.
Another back of a length ball around off and middle, blocked.
Bumper but too short. Brooks ducks under it.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one outside off, Brooks shows no interest and shoulders arms.
On off, Blackwood comes forward and keeps it out.
Shortish and around off, worked towards square leg.
On off, blocked.
Quicker one this time but Blackwood blocks it out nicely.
Five dots in a row as Blackwood once again pushes this fuller ball back to the bowler.
Slower through the air on middle and leg, Blackwood comes forward and looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Shorter length ball on middle, Brooks tucks it towards the leg side and calls for a single.
Bumper but that did not bounce too high. Blackwood ducks under it but falls down on the ground in the process.
Another one, and a good one again. Blackwood does well to evade.
Shortish and around off, blocked towards cover off the back foot.
Another back of a length ball on off, Blackwood keeps it out.
Short again but Blackwood has no problem dealing with it.
Ohh! That was close! Flighted outside off and spinning in, Brooks leaves it and is lucky as the ball spins in and just about misses the off pole.
Floated on off, Brooks keeps it out.
Shorter on off, Brooks defends it off his back foot.
Tossed up on off and middle, Brooks milks it to long on and rotates the strike.
Flighted on middle, JB plays it to mid on and gets to the other end.
Down the leg side, blocked.
Short and around middle and leg, Blackwood pulls it towards deep square leg for a single.
Shortish and around off, a solid block by Brooks off his back foot.
Nicely done! Good length ball just outside off, Brooks stays on the back foot and then dabs it down to third man for a couple.
A bouncer down the leg side. Left alone.
Shortish and around off, Brooks tucks it wide of the man at mid on for a quick single.
Shortish and around the body, worked towards fine leg for a single. Blackwood moves to 48.
Misfield and a run. Full on off and middle, Blackwood pushes it back to the bowler who fails to get down quickly and allows a single.
FOUR! Overpitched and got the punishment. Full and outside off, Brooks drills it through the covers to bag a boundary.
On off, blocked.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
SIX! This one sails over the fence. Brilliant from Brooks. Flighted ball around off, Brooks smashes it over long on for a biggie.
Full and on the pads, worked towards the leg side.
Bouncer on middle, Blackwood ducks under it.
Just short of Pope at short leg. A nice bumper from Stokes. Blackwood hops and somehow manages to block it. It wasn't too far away from Pope at short leg.
Another quality back of a length ball around the body, the rib tickler. Blackwood does well to block though.
This one is just around off, Blackwood fends it away towards point. A testing over by Stokes.
This one is way too short and Blackwood ducks under easily.
Nice bumper to end the over but Blackwood did really well to duck under. A fine over and an equally good response from Blackwood.
Short and outside off, punched to deep cover for a single.
Appeal for LBW but the umpire shakes his head. No thought of sending it upstairs. Replays show why. Big inside edge on that one.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

FIFTY FOR BLACKWOOD. Did it in the 2nd innings of the first Test and doing it here again. Can he continue though? A flatter ball on middle, Blackwood strokes it to long on and takes a single. It is his 12th Test half ton.
Full and around middle, this one is pushed towards long on for a run.
Full and around off, driven to mid on.
A bouncer on middle, Brooks thought of hammering it via a pull but left it at the last moment.
Another sharp bouncer, this time Brooks evades it nicely.
Shortish and around off, pushed towards point.
Another bouncer but this one is little too high so Brooks ducks again.
This one is down the leg side so Brooks has no issues leaving it alone.
Back of a length ball around off and middle, Brooks works it on towards deep square leg and runs through for a brace.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Fuller and around off, driven to long on for a single.
A solid front foot block back to the bowler this time by Brooks.
Full and around off, this time he whips it toward deep mid-wicket and takes two.

SIX! Gets to his half ton with a biggie! Woakes was there at long on and for a moment, his heart would have been in his mouth. Just about clears him. It is a loopy ball around off, Brooks powers it over the long on region for a biggie. Fifty in the first innings, fifty again but he needs to get to the three-figure score in this one to help West Indies secure a draw.
Shortish and around off, this time he blocks it out.

FOUR RUNNING RUNS! Nice shot but what an effort from Stokes. Runs in to bowl and delivers it around off, Blackwood punches it through mid off. There is no one manning that position so Stokes goes chasing after it. He gets near the fence and puts in a dive and pulls the ball back in. The umpires check if it is a clean stop. Well, it is a clean stop but the batters have taken four running runs. Full marks for the effort.
Bouncer, Blackwood ducks under it.
Another bouncer! Blackwood does well to evade.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Stokes is the man again. What a player! He just keeps coming at you. On the first ball of the over, he ran all the way down to long off to save a boundary and now once again bowls an effort ball. Bangs it short around the body. Blackwood tries to somehow fend it off but ends up getting it off his gloves. The ball balloons behind. Buttler charges ahead, covers a lot of ground and takes the catch with a dive forward. A fine innings from Blackwood comes to an end. And with that, TEA ON DAY 5.
Shortish around the body, Dowrich fends it off.
Shortish around off, Dowrich is behind the line to block.
Good length ball around off, Brooks works it on the leg side for a single.

OUT! Just clipping the leg stump but that will do for England. Dowrich goes without opening his account once again. 100th Test wicket for Woakes. A good length ball around off, Dowrich after facing the chin music in the last over is hoping to work it on the leg side. He moves a little towards the off side and is hit on the pad. Woakes and others put in a loud appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Dowrich takes it upstairs after having a word with Brooks. Let's see if he is safe or no. Front foot is fine. No bat involved either. Where is it hitting? Clipping the leg stump so the on-field decision stays. Dowrich has to go and England just 4 wickets away from leveling the series.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards point.
FOUR! Whipped! The skipper is off the mark in style. Full and on the pads, he flicks it powerfully through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Shortish and around off, Holder pushes it down to third man for a single.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Outside off, left alone.
Down the leg side, Holder ducks under it.
Another bouncer but again harmless one as it is down the leg side.
And another one, no problems for Holder to evade it.
Back of a length ball again and once again down the leg side. Holder lets it be again.
Landed around off and middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Length ball around off, Brooks plays it towards point.
Shortish and around off this time, Brooks keeps it out.
A good length ball on the pads, Brooks looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Shortish and around off, punched towards mid off.
Another back of a length ball around off, Brooks is solid in defense.
Shortish and around off again, blocked towards point off the back foot by Brooks.
Good length ball on middle, worked towards mid-wicket.
Shortish and on the body, tucked towards square leg by Holder.
Just short of the leg gully fielder. A well-directed bouncer from Stokes. Holder tries to play it towards the leg side but there's leg gully placed. It falls just short of that fielder.
Short but little too short so Holder ducks under it easily.
Shortish and around off, blocked.
Short again, this one is angled away. Holder fails to defend as the ball beats the outside edge.
Good length ball around off, Brooks keeps it out.
Landed on a good length on middle, played towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length ball on middle, blocked off the back foot.
Length delivery around middle, Brooks plays it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
A solid front foot block by Holder to this good length ball around off.
Good length ball around off, Holder guides it towards point.
Back of a length delivery on middle and leg, Brooks plays it back to the bowler.
Short ball on the body, Brooks sits under it.
Down the leg side, Brooks lets it be.
Bouncer on the body, Brooks ducks under it.
Length ball on off, Brooks pushes it to the off side.
Back of a length ball on off, Brooks blocks it.
Good length ball outside off, Holder shoulders arms to it. The ball comes back in but not enough to clip the stumps. Good leave by Holder.
Length ball on off, Holder gets on his font foot and defends it.
Good length delivery on off, Holder defends it.
On off, Jason defends.
Once again consistency from both Woakes and Holder. Woakes bowls it around off and Holder is calm to get behind it and defend.
Outside off, Jason leaves it alone.
Starts with a beauty! Good length ball just around off and straightens. Brooks looks to defend but misses.
Length delivery on off, Brooks blocks it properly this time.
On the pads, Brooks flicks it uppishly but in the gap at mid-wicket and gets a couple.

EDGED AND FOUR! Broad bowling it really well here but Brooks is managing to stay out in the middle. Good length ball around off, Brooks looks to defend it with soft hands but gets a thick outside edge. It goes to the right of second slip, not uppishly. Stokes dives but to no avail and the ball goes away to the fence.
Length ball on off, Brooks defends it off his back foot.
On off, Brooks defends it.
Fuller and just outside off, Holder drives it towards point and takes one.
Ripper from Woakes! How did that miss the edge? A good length ball just around off, just a hint of away movement and Brooks fails to get bat on ball.
Fuller and around off and middle, played towards mid on.
Landed around off on a length, Brooks taps it towards point.
Shortish and around off one more time, this time Brooks is on the back foot to push it to mid on.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
In the channel outside off, Holder lets it go.
Full and outside off, Holder goes for the drive but misses. Lose from the Windies skipper.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball around off and middle, Holder plays it towards mid on.

Another one goes past the outside edge. Awkward bounce as the ball goes towards keeper. Fuller and just outside off, keeps low and beats the bat to go to the keeper. Replays show that there was a little nick as the ball went past but it bounced well in front of Buttler.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards point.
Good length ball outside off, guided towards point.
Down the leg side, Brooks looks to flick it towards fine leg but fails to connect. Buttler does well to move to his left and gather the ball.
Fuller and around off, Brooks is solid on his front foot block.
Goes full this time and Brooks drives him through covers. Two more for him before mid off can come around.
In the channel outside off, Brooks lets that one pass to the keeper.
Good length ball on off, blocked solidly.
Back of a length ball around off, Holder keeps it out.
Another solid front foot block by Holder to this length ball on off.

EDGY FOUR! This will be frustrating for Broad. Length delivery just outside off, Holder waits for it and then at the last moment runs it down to third man and the ball reaches the fence. He played it with soft hands there.
Full and around off, pushed to mid off.

FOUR! This time off the inside edge! Shake of head from Broad. Good length ball outside off, Holder goes on the back foot and looks to punch it but gets an inside edge. The ball goes over the stumps and down to the fine leg fence.
Shortish and around off, blocked.
Good length ball angled in, Brooks though is confident that he has his stumps covered and leaves it alone. Replays show it wasn't too far from the top of off.
Fuller and around off, blocked.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Good length ball around off, Brooks keeps it out.

OUT! LBW! Super Sam does it again. This young lad has a golden arm and he has got the big wicket of Shamarh Brooks. The wicket England were desperately looking for and Curran has given Root that. Brilliant bowling from Sam, he comes around the wicket and pitches it around off. The change of angle works as the ball comes in off the deck. Brooks looks to defend off his back foot but misses and gets stuck on the crease. The ball hits him on his back pad. The English players put in a huge appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Brooks has a word with Holder but opts against review. Would not have mattered as replays later on show that it was hitting the wickets on umpire's call.
Outside off, Roach leaves it alone. End of a successful over by Curran.

Not Out! Holder is back in safely! On the pads, Holder flicks it to the left of deep mid-wicket. Holder looks for two straightaway. The fielder is quick to get to the ball but Holder's long strides see him make his ground.
Outside off, Holder leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Holder defends it.
Another mix up but safe again. Length ball on off, Holder taps it towards point and comes out for a run but Roach sends him back.
On the pads, Holder glances it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Good length ball on off, Roach defends it by getting right behind it.
Length ball on off, Holder defends it.
Good length ball on off, Holder blocks.
On the stump, Jason defends it.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On middle and leg, Holder glances it to the leg side.
Length ball on off, JH defends it and gets through the over. Good news for England is Roach will be on strike to begin Broad's over.
Fuller on off and middle, Roach defends it off his front foot.
Full and straight on the stumps, Roach gets his body behind it and defends it.
Outside off, Roach keeps his bat hanging on off pole so it goes away from it.
Another solid block from Roach as he keeps this full ball out.
Full on the stumps, Kemar is happy to defend it with minimum of fuss.
Length ball on middle and leg, Roach gets his bat behind it and sees off the over.
FOUR! Very good shot and was always in control. Short ball around the belly, Holder pulls it through backward square leg for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Holder looks to defend but it goes off the inner half of his bat towards fine leg for a single.
Full outside off, Roach looks to drive but misses.
On the pads, Roach flicks it on the on side and gets off the mark with a single.
Very full on off, Holder defends it.
Full on off, Holder defends it towards mid on.
Floated on off, Roach blocks it.
Full toss outside off, Roach drives it to mid off.
Tossed up on off, Roach defends it.
Darted on the pads, Roach looks to whip it but misses and gets hit on the pads. Stifled appeal but nothing.
Flighted on off, Roach blocks it.
Tossed up on off, Kemar defends it.
Good length ball outside off, Holder plays it to point.
Length ball on off, Holder defends it.
On the pads, Holder flicks it in front of square and looks for two straight away. He gets it with ease.
Bouncer but down the leg side, Holder ducks.
Outside off, Holder leaves it alone.
On middle, Holder plays it to mid on and gets a single.
Floated on off, Holder looks to defend but it goes off the outer half of his bat towards backward point.
FOUR! Bess gives him a gift wrapped full toss. Holder says thank you very much and drives it through covers for a boundary.
SIX! Woah! Out of nowhere Holder has taken on Bess. Tossed up on off, Holder smashes it over long on for a biggie.
Darted around the pads, Holder flicks it away from short leg.

OUT! Bowled! Bess has the last laugh and he has bowled a beauty to get rid of the West Indies skipper. A perfect off spinners Test wicket. Bess gives this air and bowls it on the rough outside off, Holder looks to defend but the ball spins right between the gate of bat and pad to hit the top of middle and leg. England just 2 wickets away now.
Floated on off, Joseph pushes it on the off side and gets a single. 11 from the over but that does not matter as it also got the massive wicket of Holder.
Bouncer on the leg side, Joseph sits under it.
Another short one on top of middle and leg, Joseph ducks under it.
On the pads, Joseph looks to flick but misses. The ball lobs off his thigh pad but falls short of Ollie Pope.
On top of middle and leg, Alzarri looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
FOUR! Gorgeous shot from Alzarri. This man can bat. Overpitched on middle and off, Joseph gets on his front foot and drives it through mid on for a boundary.
Full on off, Joseph pushes it to the left of Stokes. He gets the ball and sends a wild throw which goes over the head of Joseph and away from Buttler to let them take a single.

NOT OUT! England lose their review and more importantly Joseph survives. Flighted on off, Joseph leaves it alone and gets hit on the pads. The England players appeal and the umpire turns it down. Root signals the 'T'. Replay rolls in and it shows that the ball is going onto miss the stumps.

NOT OUT! Good review from Alzarri. Tossed up on middle and off, Joseph looks to defend but misses and the ball lobs off his pad to Ollie Pope at short leg. Bess and his teammates appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Joseph takes the review straightaway. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge shows there was no bat involved hence Alzarri was so confident. Ball Tracker then comes on and it shows that the ball is missing the stumps.
Floated on off, Alzarri pushes it to cover.
Floated on off, Joseph plays a wild shot to long on and gets a single.
Tossed up on off, Roach defends it.
Flighted on off, KM defends it to get through the over.
Play and a miss! A shortish length ball just outside off. Joseph looks to punch off the back foot misses.
Short ball down the leg side. Joseph ducks under it.
Full and outside off, Joseph smashes it through covers and takes two.
Ouch! Where did that hit? Stokes thinks it's too high. Joseph there was expecting a back of a length ball but it wasn't. It comes back in and hits him high on the pads.
Nearly onto the stumps. A good length ball around off, Joseph looks to defend but gets an inside edge and the ball just about misses the stumps.

OUT! Caught! 9 down and England need just one wicket. Not a shot that West Indies would have wanted to see. Fuller ball outside off, Alzarri cannot stray away from his natural game with the willow as he goes for the drive. He hits it uppishly and straight to Bess at point. He takes a simple catch. One wicket away from leveling the series are England.
On the pads, Roach looks to defend but it goes off his pads behind square on the leg side and they take two leg byes.
Floated outside off, Roach looks to defend but misses.
Tossed up on off, Roach manages to block it.
Flighted on off, Roach looks to defend but gets it off the outside edge. Luckily for him it falls short of Stokes at first slip.
On the stumps, Roach defends it.
Floated off spinner, Roach looks to defend but it goes towards leg gully off the upper half. No man there so Roach is safe.
Good length ball on off, Gabriel defends it.
Bouncer! Gabriel sits under it.
Another short ball, Gabriel once again ducks.
Stokes bowls it full and straight but messes up his line and bowls it down the leg side. No problem for Gabriel to leave that one.
Floated on off, Gabriel defends it.
Off spinner on off, Gabriel pushes it to mid on.
Floated on off, Roach flicks it to the leg side.
Flighted outside off, Roach looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is a appeal but turned down as the impact looked outside off.
Floated outside off, Roach looks to defend but misses.
On middle and leg, Roach looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Tossed up outside off, Roach looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads.
FOUR! Bess comes around the wicket and bows it on middle and leg, Roach gets down on one knee and sweeps it through square leg for a boundary.
Floated on off, Gabriel plays it to mid on.
Tossed up outside off, Gabriel looks to defend but misses.
Floated outside off, Gabriel looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
On the stumps, SG defends it.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Flighted outside off, Gabriel looks to defend but misses.

OUT! Caught! Ollie Pope takes a stunner at short leg to seal the game! Floated delivery on middle and leg, Roach flicks it to the left of short leg. Pope gets a hand to it and the ball lobs away from him. He dives and takes a beauty to seal the game. ENGLAND WIN BY 113 RUNS!
